%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael%2Ft-19067044%5C%22%3EIsrael%3C%2Fa%3E%E2%80%98s%20foreign%20minister%20Eli%20Cohen%20thanked%20the%20US%20for%20its%20vote%20against%20a%20resolution%20calling%20for%20a%20humanitarian%20cease-fire%20in%20Gaza.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CWith%20gratitude%20to%20our%20ally%2C%20the%20US%2C%20for%20its%20support%20to%20continue%20the%20fight%20to%20bring%20the%20hostages%20home%20and%20to%20eliminate%20the%20Hamas%20terrorist%20organisation%2C%20which%20will%20bring%20a%20better%20future%20to%20the%20region%2C%E2%80%9D%20Cohen%20wrote%20on%20Twitter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CA%20cease-fire%20at%20this%20time%20would%20prevent%20the%20collapse%20of%20the%20Hamas%20terrorist%20organisation%2C%20which%20is%20committing%20war%20crimes%20and%20crimes%20against%20humanity%2C%20and%20would%20enable%20it%20to%20continue%20ruling%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20senior%20Hamas%20official%20Izzat%20al-Rishq%20said%20in%20a%20statement%20the%20group%2C%20designated%20a%20terrorist%20organisation%20by%20the%20US%20and%20others%2C%20strongly%20condemned%20the%20US%20veto.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20US%20obstruction%20of%20the%20issuance%20of%20a%20cease-fire%20resolution%20is%20a%20direct%20participation%20with%20%5BIsrael%5D%C2%A0in%20killing%20our%20people%20and%20committing%20more%20massacres%20and%20ethnic%20cleansing%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECohen%20again%20criticised%20UN%20Secretary-General%20Antonio%20Guterres%20and%20his%20decision%20to%20invoke%20Article%2099%20of%20the%20UN%20Charter%20and%20formally%20warn%20the%20Security%20Council%20of%20a%20global%20threat%20from%20the%20war.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fisrael-hamas-war-live-blog-dec-6%2Flive-67643127%5C%22%3EThat%20decision%20led%20to%20Friday%E2%80%99s%20session%20and%20vote%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CGuterres%E2%80%