20Saturday%20Washington%20and%20its%20Asia%20allies%20would%20%26quot%3Bstand%20up%26quot%3B%20for%20stability%20across%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%2C%20and%20reiterated%20their%20commitment%20to%20freedom%20of%20navigation%20in%20the%20disputed%20South%20China%20Sea.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20continue%20to%20stand%20up%20for%20peace%20and%20stability%20across%20the%20Taiwan%20Strait%20and%20freedom%20of%20navigation%20in%20the%20east%20and%20South%20China%20Seas%2C%26quot%3B%20Sullivan%20told%20reporters%20in%20Seoul%2C%20alongside%20South%20Korea's%20Cho%20Tae-yong%20and%20Japan's%20Takeo%20Akiba.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fwashington-allies-to-stand-up-for-stability-in-taiwan-strait-us%2Farticleshow%2F105853966.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20UK%20PM%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20New%20Anti-Immigration%20Policy%20Has%20Put%20Him%20In%20Jeopardy%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EUK%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20position%20is%20in%20jeopardy%20after%20backlash%20from%20his%20party%20over%20his%20government's%20controversial%20anti-immigration%20plan.%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20attempt%20to%20cut%20soaring%20immigration%20in%20the%20country%20met%20with%20the%20resignation%20of%20Robert%20Jenrick%2C%20the%20UK's%20immigration%20minister.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E'Stop%20The%20Boats'%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%20unveiled%20his%20plan%2C%20%26quot%3BStop%20The%20Boats%26quot%3B%2C%20to%20send%20asylum%20seekers%20to%20Rwanda.%20The%20attempt%20seems%20to%20pull%20the%20Conservative%20Party%20in%20opposite%20directions%20due%20to%20differences%20in%20opinions%20between%20the%20hardliners%20and%20moderates.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20stakes%20for%20the%20country%20are%20too%20high%20for%20us%20not%20to%20pursue%20the%20stronger%20protections%20required%20to%20end%20the%20merry-go-round%20of%20legal%20challenges%20which%20risk%20paralysing%20the%20scheme%20and%20negating%20its%20intended%20deterrent%2C%26quot%3B%20Robert%20Jenrick%20wrote%20in%20his%20resignation%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20his%20reply%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak%20said%2C%20Jenkin's%20%26quot%3BOpposition%20to%20it%20was%20%26quot%3Bbased%20on%20a%20fundamental%20misunderstanding%20of%20the%20situation%26quot%3B.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20June%2C%20the%20Court%20of%20Appeal%20ruled%20the%20UK%20government's%20plan%20to%20send%20asylum%20seekers%20to%20Rwanda%20was%20unlawful%20as%20the%20African%20nation%20could%20not%20be%20considered%20a%20safe%20third%20country.%20The%20UK%20Supreme%20Court%20in%20November%20agreed%20with%20the%20ruling%20and%20said%20Rwanda%20is%20not%20a%20safe%20third%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%2C%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20administration%20published%20emergency%20legislation%20to%20ensure%20Rwanda%20is%20considered%20a%20safe%20country.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20legislation%20will%20be%20put%20to%20vote%20on%20December%2012.%20Some%20members%20of%20parliament%20in%20his%20party%20said%20for%20the%20first%20time%20since%20Sunak%20entered%20office%20a%20year%20ago%20there%20was%20a%20possibility%20he%20could%20face%20a%20leadership%20challenge%2C%20Reuters%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20far%20only%20one%20Conservative%20Party%20MP%2C%20Andrea%20Jenkyns%2C%20has%20publicly%20called%20for%20a%20no-confidence%20vote%20against%20Rishi%20Sunak%2C%20but%20she%20said%20six%20of%20her%20colleagues%20have%20done%20so%20privately.%20Tories%20lag%20way%20behind%20the%20Labour%20Party%20in%20opinion%20polls%20of%20the%20elections%20in%20January%202025.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENo%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%20has%20succeeded%20in%20completing%20their%20full%20term%20in%20office%20since%20the%20resignation%20of%20former%20Prime%20Minister%20David%20Cameron%20post-Brexit.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Immigration%20Plan%20And%20How%20It%20Affects%20Indians%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20UK%20government's%20latest%20set%20of%20visa%20crackdowns%20to%20cut%20immigration%20figures%20includes%20a%20major%20hike%20in%20the%20minimum%20salary%20threshold%20for%20British%20nationals%20and%20permanent%20residents%20applying%20to%20bring%20family%20members%20to%20join%20them%20in%20the%20UK%2C%20a%20move%20expected%20to%20impact%20several%20Indian%20families.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20new%20immigration%20crackdown%2C%20overseas%20care%20workers%20will%20be%20banned%20from%20bringing%20family%20members%20and%20skilled%20professionals%20must%20meet%20an%20annual%20salary%20threshold%20of%20GBP%2038%2C700%2C%20up%20from%20the%20current%20GBP%2026%2C200.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20stop%20immigration%20undercutting%20the%20salary%20of%20British%20workers%2C%26quot%3B%20UK%20Home%20Secretary%20James%20Cleverly%20told%20lawmakers.%20%26quot%3BWe%20will%20create%20a%20new%20immigration%20salary%20list%20with%20a%20reduced%20number%20of%20occupations%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalysts%20have%20flagged%20that%20this%20steep%20hike%20will%20have%20a%20wide-ranging%20impact%20on%20the%20family%20plans%20of%20those%20on%20lower%20incomes.%20Business%20and%20trade%20unions%20flagged%20the%20measures%20as%20counterproductive%20due%20to%20labour%20shortage%20and%20slow%20growth%20in%20the%20economy.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndian%20industry%20and%20student%20groups%20have%20warned%20the%20UK%20PM-led%20government%20of%20%26quot%3Bunintended%20consequences%26quot%3B%20of%20the%20new%20measures%2C%20which%20would%20lead%20to%20skilled%20Indians%20choosing%20alternate%20economies.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702093440000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2023-11%2Fotenbt1o_rishi-sunak-reuters_625x300_10_November_23.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-rwanda-bill-visa-measures-have-put-uk-pm-rishi-sunaks-position-in-jeopardy-4648352%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22UK%20Prime%20Minister%20Rishi%20Sunak's%20position%20is%20in%20jeopardy%20after%20backlash%20from%20his%20party%20over%20his%20government's%20controversial%20anti-immigration%20plan.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-rwanda-bill-visa-measures-have-put-uk-pm-rishi-sunaks-position-in-jeopardy-4648352%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-rwanda-bill-visa-measures-have-put-uk-pm-rishi-sunaks-position-in-jeopardy-4648352%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fhow-rwanda-bill-visa-measures-have-put-uk-pm-rishi-sunaks-position-in-jeopardy-4648352%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Why%20And%20How%20'Dimming%20The%20Sun'%20To%20Fight%20Climate%20Change%20Is%20A%20Possibility%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EIt's%20becoming%20increasingly%20clear%20that%20we%20will%20fail%20to%20meet%20our%20climate%20goals.%20We%20were%20already%20at%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fd41586-023-03775-z%5C%22%3E1.26%C2%B0C%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20warming%20in%202022%20and%20are%20on%20track%20to%20blow%20through%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcds.climate.copernicus.eu%2Fapps%2Fc3s%2Fapp-c3s-global-temperature-trend-monitor%3Fmonth%3Afloat%3D10%26year%3Afloat%3D2023%5C%22%3E1.5%C2%B0C%20in%20the%20mid-2030s%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Research%20even%20suggests%20that%20current%20climate%20policy%20will%20lead%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fclimateactiontracker.org%2Fglobal%2Fcat-thermometer%2F%5C%22%3Emore%20than%202.5%C2%B0C%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20warming%20by%20the%20end%20of%20this%20century.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWarming%20of%20this%20magnitude%20would%20devastate%20vulnerable%20communities%20and%20ecosystems%20around%20the%20world.%20It's%20time%20we%20consider%20something%20radically%20new%20that%20could%20stop%20climate%20change%20in%20its%20tracks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20powerful%20volcanic%20eruptions%2C%20like%20Tambora%20(Indonesia)%20in%201815%20and%20Pinatubo%20(Philippines)%20in%201991%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fscied.ucar.edu%2Flearning-zone%2Fhow-climate-works%2Fhow-volcanoes-influence-climate%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DVolcanic%2520ash%2520or%2520dust%2520released%2Ccools%2520the%2520area%2520directly%2520below.%5C%22%3Eglobal%20temperatures%20dip%3C%2Fa%3E%20for%20a%20few%20years.%20Major%20eruptions%20create%20a%20hazy%20layer%20of%20microscopic%20particles%20in%20the%20upper%20atmosphere%20that%20last%20for%20several%20years%2C%20dimming%20the%20Sun%20temporarily.%20We%20could%20copy%20this%20effect%20to%20fight%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Earth%20is%20warmed%20by%20the%20Sun%2C%20but%20it%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nasa.gov%2Fcenters-and-facilities%2Flangley%2Fwhat-is-earths-energy-budget-five-questions-with-a-guy-who-knows%2F%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DEarth%2527s%2520energy%2520budget%253F-%2CEarth%2527s%2520energy%2520budget%2520describes%2520the%2520balance%2520between%2520the%2520radiant%2520energy%2Cportion%2520of%2520the%2520electromagnetic%2520spectrum.%5C%22%3Ekept%20warm%20by%20greenhouse%20gases%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20trap%20the%20heat%20our%20planet%20gives%20off.%20The%20warming%20effect%20of%20our%20CO%E2%82%82%20emissions%20could%20be%20countered%20by%20creating%20a%20persistent%2C%20artificial%20haze%20like%20those%20seen%20following%20major%20volcanic%20eruptions.%20Research%20has%20found%20that%20we%20would%20only%20need%20to%20dim%20the%20Sun%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1002%2Fjgrd.50646%5C%22%3Eby%20around%201%25%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20cool%20the%20planet%20by%201%C2%B0C.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20may%20sound%20unlikely.%20But%20every%20engineering%20assessment%20to%20date%20has%20concluded%20that%20it%20would%20be%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fiopscience.iop.org%2Farticle%2F10.1088%2F1748-9326%2Faba7e7%2Fmeta%5C%22%3Efeasible%20and%20relatively%20cheap%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20do%20using%20a%20fleet%20of%20high-flying%20jets%20to%20release%20reflective%20particles%20into%20the%20upper%20atmosphere.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%20we%20could%20dim%20the%20Sun%20%E2%80%93%20but%20should%20we%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563617%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-23-pz9rq2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D1000%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Ash%20cloud%20of%20Pinatubo%20during%20the%201991%20eruption.%5C%22%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563617%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-23-pz9rq2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D402%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563617%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-23-pz9rq2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D402%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563617%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-23-pz9rq2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D402%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563617%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-23-pz9rq2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D505%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563617%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-23-pz9rq2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D505%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563617%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-23-pz9rq2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D505%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563617%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-23-pz9rq2.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%5Cn%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cspan%3EAsh%20cloud%20of%20Pinatubo%20during%20the%201991%20eruption.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcommons.wikimedia.org%2Fwiki%2FFile%3APinatubo_ash_plume_910612.jpg%5C%22%3EDave%20Harlow%20%2F%20US%20Geological%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby-nc-sa%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3ECC%20BY-NC-SA%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ECooling%20the%20planet%20would%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDimming%20the%20Sun%20wouldn't%20perfectly%20reverse%20climate%20change.%20The%20Sun's%20warming%20effect%20is%20strongest%20during%20the%20day%2C%20in%20the%20summer%20and%20at%20the%20Tropics%2C%20whereas%20greenhouse%20gases%20warm%20everywhere%20and%20at%20all%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20we%20could%20create%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1029%2F2019JD030329%5C%22%3Ean%20even%20cooling%20effect%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20world%20by%20adjusting%20where%20we%20release%20the%20particles.%20Research%20suggests%20that%20such%20an%20approach%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Froyalsocietypublishing.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1098%2Frsta.2016.0454%5C%22%3Egreatly%20reduce%20climate%20risks%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERising%20temperatures%20really%20matter.%20Species%20around%20the%20world%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1126%2Fscience.aai9214%3Fcasa_token%3D2qPuH36buhAAAAAA%253AJM9WQcq2tEqIVUDc6yqWP5AOcXOzenwYhY9BCkZAE37QXjk-ndpn-JcqLzjjIxQmAuF88r9G0f2plA%5C%22%3Eon%20the%20move%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20tracking%20familiar%20temperatures%20polewards%20as%20the%20planet%20warms%20up.%20But%20many%20won't%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20pace%20with%20the%20changing%20climate%20and%20others%20have%20nowhere%20to%20go%2C%20so%20extinctions%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.science.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1126%2Fscience.aaa4984%5C%22%3Eprojected%20to%20increase%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20also%20seeing%20extreme%20heat%20that%20is%20edging%20closer%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.pnas.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1073%2Fpnas.2316003120%5C%22%3Eabsolute%20limits%20of%20the%20human%20body%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20putting%20lives%20at%20risk%20and%20limiting%20outdoor%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20the%20planet%20heats%20up%2C%20warmer%20air%20is%20drawing%20more%20moisture%20from%20the%20soil%20in%20dry%20times%2C%20and%20dumping%20more%20out%20at%20once%20when%20it%20rains.%20This%20is%20making%20dry%20regions%20drier%2C%20wet%20regions%20wetter%2C%20and%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs44221-023-00047-y%5C%22%3Eintensifying%20both%20droughts%20and%20floods%3C%2Fa%3E%20across%20the%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDimming%20the%20Sun%20would%20offset%20this%20effect.%20But%20it%20would%20still%20alter%20global%20wind%20and%20rainfall%20patterns.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EResearch%20indicates%20that%20this%20would%20mean%20smaller%20rainfall%20changes%20overall.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs41558-019-0398-8%5C%22%3Ea%20small%20minority%20of%20places%3C%2Fa%3E%20could%20see%20more%20pronounced%20changes%20in%20rainfall%20compared%20to%20what%20they%20would%20face%20under%20climate%20change.%20Climate%20models%20disagree%20on%20the%20details%20of%20regional%20rainfall%20changes%2C%20so%20it's%20unclear%20at%20this%20stage%20which%20regions%20would%20see%20the%20greatest%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBlocking%20some%20sunlight%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1029%2F2023EF003679%5C%22%3Ewould%20also%20be%20an%20effective%3C%2Fa%3E%20way%20of%20keeping%20icy%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20frozen.%20Rising%20temperatures%20are%20causing%20the%20Antarctic%20and%20Greenland%20ice%20sheets%20to%20melt%20at%20an%20accelerating%20rate%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.climate.gov%2Fnews-features%2Funderstanding-climate%2Fclimate-change-global-sea-level%5C%22%3Edriving%20up%20the%20global%20sea%20level%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Climate%20change%20is%20also%20thawing%20permafrost%20(frozen%20soil%20that%20stores%20vast%20amounts%20of%20carbon)%20leading%20to%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nature.com%2Farticles%2Fs43017-021-00230-3%5C%22%3Eemission%20of%20more%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20methane%20and%20CO%E2%82%82.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563619%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-22-4p9vrw.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D1000%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20alt%3D%5C%22Broken%20pieces%20of%20Arctic%20sea%20ice.%5C%22%20sizes%3D%5C%22(min-width%3A%201466px)%20754px%2C%20(max-width%3A%20599px)%20100vw%2C%20(min-width%3A%20600px)%20600px%2C%20237px%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563619%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-22-4p9vrw.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D398%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20600w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563619%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-22-4p9vrw.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D398%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563619%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-22-4p9vrw.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D600%26amp%3Bh%3D398%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%201800w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563619%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-22-4p9vrw.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D45%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D501%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D1%20754w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563619%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-22-4p9vrw.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D30%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D501%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D2%201508w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563619%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-22-4p9vrw.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26amp%3Bq%3D15%26amp%3Bauto%3Dformat%26amp%3Bw%3D754%26amp%3Bh%3D501%26amp%3Bfit%3Dcrop%26amp%3Bdpr%3D3%202262w%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fimages.theconversation.com%2Ffiles%2F563619%2Foriginal%2Ffile-20231205-22-4p9vrw.jpg%3Fixlib%3Drb-1.1.0%26q%3D45%26auto%3Dformat%26w%3D754%26fit%3Dclip%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%5Cn%3Cfigcaption%3E%3Cspan%3EMelting%20ice%20can%20accelerate%20the%20pace%20of%20global%20warming.%3C%2Fspan%3E%20%3Cspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.flickr.com%2Fphotos%2Fusgeologicalsurvey%2F4370267907%2Fin%2Fset-72157623467470824%5C%22%3EUS%20Geological%20Survey%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22http%3A%2F%2Fcreativecommons.org%2Flicenses%2Fby-nc-sa%2F4.0%2F%5C%22%3ECC%20BY-NC-SA%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ESide%20effects%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAlthough%20dimming%20the%20Sun%20could%20keep%20the%20Earth%20cool%2C%20it%20would%20not%20deal%20with%20the%20root%20of%20the%20climate%20problem%3A%20the%20buildup%20of%20CO%E2%82%82%20and%20other%20greenhouse%20gases%20in%20the%20atmosphere.%20CO%E2%82%82%20not%20only%20warms%20the%20planet%2C%20it%20also%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Foceanservice.noaa.gov%2Ffacts%2Facidification.html%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DOcean%2520acidification%2520refers%2520to%2520a%2CCO2%2520from%2520the%2520atmosphere.%5C%22%3Eacidifies%20the%20ocean%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20making%20it%20harder%20for%20corals%20and%20other%20creatures%20to%20form%20their%20shells.%20Dimming%20the%20Sun%20wouldn't%20change%20this.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20would%20bring%20about%20some%20side%20effects%20as%20well.%20This%20hazy%20layer%20of%20particles%20would%20make%20the%20sky%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1029%2F2012GL051652%5C%22%3Ea%20little%20whiter%3C%2Fa%3E.%20And%20if%20we%20copy%20volcanic%20eruptions%20by%20releasing%20sulphate%20particles%20to%20the%20upper%20atmosphere%2C%20then%20we'd%20also%20be%20adding%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.epa.gov%2Facidrain%2Fwhat-acid-rain%23%3A%257E%3Atext%3DAcid%2520rain%2520results%2520when%2520sulfur%2Cform%2520sulfuric%2520and%2520nitric%2520acids.%5C%22%3Ethe%20acid%20rain%20problem%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20particles%20could%20impact%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.eea.europa.eu%2Fen%2Ftopics%2Fin-depth%2Fclimate-change-mitigation-reducing-emissions%2Fcurrent-state-of-the-ozone-layer%5C%22%3Ethe%20ozone%20layer%3C%2Fa%3E%20too%2C%20which%20protects%20us%20from%20harmful%20UV%20rays.%20Research%20suggests%20that%20adding%20more%20sulphate%20particles%20to%20the%20upper%20atmosphere%20would%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fagupubs.onlinelibrary.wiley.com%2Fdoi%2Ffull%2F10.1029%2F2021GL094058%5C%22%3Edelay%20the%20slow%20recovery%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20ozone%20hole.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20side%20effects%20are%20a%20concern.%20But%20they%20pale%20in%20comparison%20to%20the%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change.%20A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmedia.rff.org%2Fdocuments%2FWP_23-23.pdf%5C%22%3Erecent%20study%3C%2Fa%3E%20found%20that%20the%20benefit%20of%20reduced%20extreme%20heat%20for%20human%20health%20could%20outweigh%20the%20health%20impacts%20of%20these%20side-effects%20by%20more%20than%2050%20to%201.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPaul%20Crutzen%2C%20who%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.nobelprize.org%2Fprizes%2Fchemistry%2F1995%2Fcrutzen%2Ffacts%2F%5C%22%3Ewon%20a%20Nobel%20prize%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%201995%20for%20solving%20the%20chemistry%20of%20the%20ozone%20hole%2C%20was%20well%20aware%20of%20these%20side%20effects%20but%20nevertheless%20argued%20that%20we%20should%20start%20taking%20the%20idea%20of%20dimming%20the%20Sun%20seriously.%20In%20an%20article%20from%202006%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.proquest.com%2Fdocview%2F198512444%3Fpq-origsite%3Dgscholar%26fromopenview%3Dtrue%5C%22%3Ehe%20stressed%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20it%20would%20be%20best%20to%20cut%20CO%E2%82%82%20emissions%20rapidly%20so%20that%20we%20wouldn't%20need%20to%20consider%20dimming%20the%20Sun%20at%20all.%20However%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.independent.co.uk%2Fclimate-change%2Fnews%2Fscientist-publishes-escape-route-from-global-warming-409981.html%5C%22%3Ehe%20lamented%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20%E2%80%9Ccurrently%2C%20this%20looks%20like%20a%20pious%20wish%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3ESymptoms%20matter%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt's%20becoming%20increasingly%20clear%20that%20this%20%E2%80%9Cpious%20wish%E2%80%9D%20isn't%20coming%20true.%20Since%20Crutzen's%202006%20article%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fessd.copernicus.org%2Farticles%2F14%2F4811%2F2022%2F%5C%22%3ECO%E2%82%82%20emissions%3C%2Fa%3E%20have%20surged%20by%20more%20than%2015%25.%20We%20just%20aren't%20cutting%20emissions%20fast%20enough%20to%20prevent%20climate%20change%20from%20wreaking%20terrible%20damage.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDimming%20the%20Sun%20would%20not%20address%20the%20root%20cause%20of%20the%20climate%20disease%2C%20and%20we%20must%20keep%20pushing%20to%20cut%20emissions%2C%20but%20a%20growing%20body%20of%20evidence%20suggests%20that%20it%20would%20work%20surprisingly%20well%20at%20treating%20the%20symptoms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20this%20is%20not%20so%20surprising.%20Ice%20melts%20when%20it%20is%20warm%2C%20hotter%20air%20carries%20more%20moisture%20and%20heat%20has%20a%20direct%20impact%20on%20life.%20We%20are%20far%20from%20knowing%20enough%20to%20recommend%20dimming%20the%20Sun%20today%2C%20but%20if%20countries%20don't%20start%20taking%20this%20idea%20seriously%20we%20may%20miss%20a%20valuable%20opportunity%20to%20reduce%20the%20risks%20of%20climate%20change.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EDon't%20have%20time%20to%20read%20about%20climate%20change%20as%20much%20as%20you'd%20like%3F%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%3Cem%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fuk%2Fnewsletters%2Fimagine-57%3Futm_source%3DTCUK%26utm_medium%3Dlinkback%26utm_campaign%3DImagine%26utm_content%3DDontHaveTimeTop%5C%22%3EGet%20a%20weekly%20roundup%20in%20your%20inbox%20instead.%3C%2Fa%3E%20Every%20Wednesday%2C%20The%20Conversation's%20environment%20editor%20writes%20Imagine%2C%20a%20short%20email%20that%20goes%20a%20little%20deeper%20into%20just%20one%20climate%20issue.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fuk%2Fnewsletters%2Fimagine-57%3Futm_source%3DTCUK%26utm_medium%3Dlinkback%26utm_campaign%3DImagine%26utm_content%3DDontHaveTimeBottom%5C%22%3EJoin%20the%2020%2C000%2B%20readers%20who've%20subscribed%20so%20far.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cimg%20referrerpolicy%3D%5C%22no-referrer-when-downgrade%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcounter.theconversation.com%2Fcontent%2F218670%2Fcount.gif%3Fdistributor%3Drepublish-lightbox-basic%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22The%20Conversation%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Chr%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3Cstrong%3EAuthor%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Fprofiles%2Fpeter-irvine-1233411%5C%22%3EPeter%20Irvine%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Lecturer%20in%20Earth%20Sciences%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftheconversation.com%2Finstitutions%2Fucl-1885%5C%22%3EUCL%3C%2Fa%3E)%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E%3Cspan%3E(%3Cstrong%3EDisclosure%20Statement%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fem%3E%20Peter%20Irvine%20receives%20funding%20from%20Horizon%20Europe.%20He%20acts%20as%20a%20scientific%20advisor%20to%20the