elebrated%20directors%20including%20Peter%20Bogdanovich%20on%20%26quot%3BPaper%20Moon%26quot%3B%20and%20Stanley%20Kubrick%20on%20%26quot%3BBarry%20Lyndon.%20He%20often%20used%20his%20boyish%2C%20blond%20good%20looks%20to%20play%20men%20who%20hid%20shadowy%20or%20sinister%20backgrounds%20behind%20their%20clean-cut%20images.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Neal%20maintained%20a%20steady%20television%20acting%20career%20into%20his%2070s%20in%20the%202010s%2C%20appearing%20for%20stints%20on%20%26quot%3BBones%26quot%3B%20and%20%26quot%3BDesperate%20Housewives%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20his%20longtime%20relationship%20with%20Farrah%20Fawcett%20and%20his%20tumultuous%20family%20life%20kept%20him%20in%20news.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETwice%20divorced%2C%20O'Neal%20was%20romantically%20involved%20with%20Fawcett%20for%20nearly%2030%20years%2C%20and%20they%20had%20a%20son%2C%20Redmond%2C%20born%20in%201985.%20The%20couple%20split%20in%201997%2C%20but%20reunited%20a%20few%20years%20later.%20He%20remained%20by%20Fawcett's%20side%20as%20she%20battled%20cancer%2C%20which%20killed%20her%20in%202009%20at%20age%2062.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20first%20wife%2C%20Joanna%20Moore%2C%20O'Neal%20fathered%20actors%20Griffin%20O'Neal%20and%20Tatum%20O'Neal%2C%20his%20co-star%20in%20the%201973%20movie%20%26quot%3BPaper%20Moon%2C%26quot%3B%20for%20which%20she%20won%20an%20Oscar%20for%20best%20supporting%20actress.%20He%20had%20son%20Patrick%20with%20his%20second%20wife%2C%20Leigh%20Taylor-Young.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERyan%20O'Neal%20had%20his%20own%20best-actor%20Oscar%20nomination%20for%20the%201970%20tear-jerker%20drama%20%26quot%3BLove%20Story%2C%26quot%3B%20co-starring%20Ali%20MacGraw%2C%20about%20a%20young%20couple%20who%20fall%20in%20love%2C%20marry%20and%20discover%20she%20is%20dying%20of%20cancer.%20The%20movie%20includes%20the%20memorable%2C%20but%20often%20satirized%20line%3A%20%26quot%3BLove%20means%20never%20having%20to%20say%20you're%20sorry.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20actor%20had%20at%20times%20strained%20relationships%20with%20three%20of%20his%20children%2C%20including%20estrangement%20from%20his%20daughter%2C%20squabbles%20with%20son%20Griffin%20and%20a%20drug-related%20arrest%20sparked%20by%20a%20probation%20check%20of%20his%20son%20Redmond.%20The%20personal%20drama%20often%20over-shadowed%20his%20later%20career%2C%20although%20his%20attempts%20to%20reconcile%20with%20Tatum%20O'Neal%20were%20turned%20into%20a%20short-lived%20reality%20series.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Neal%20played%20bit%20parts%20and%20performed%20some%20stunt%20work%20before%20claiming%20a%20lead%20role%20on%20the%20prime-time%20soap%20opera%20%26quot%3BPeyton%20Place%26quot%3B%20(1964-69)%2C%20which%20also%20made%20a%20star%20of%20Mia%20Farrow.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFrom%20there%20O'Neal%20jumped%20to%20the%20big%20screen%20with%201969's%20%26quot%3BThe%20Big%20Bounce%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20co-stared%20his%20then-wife%2C%20Leigh%20Taylor-Young.%20But%20it%20was%20%26quot%3BLove%20Story%26quot%3B%20that%20made%20him%20a%20movie%20star.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20romantic%20melodrama%20became%20one%20of%20Paramount%20Pictures'%20biggest%20hits%20and%20collected%20seven%20Oscar%20nominations%2C%20including%20one%20for%20best%20picture.%20It%20won%20for%20best%20music.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Neal%20then%20starred%20for%20Bogdanovich%20as%20a%20bumbling%20professor%20opposite%20Barbra%20Streisand%20in%20the%201972%20screwball%20comedy%20%26quot%3BWhat's%20Up%2C%20Doc%3F%26quot%3B%20The%20filmmaker%20cast%20him%20the%20next%20year%20in%20the%20Depression-era%20con%20artist%20comedy%20%26quot%3BPaper%20Moon.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Neal%20played%20an%20unscrupulous%20Bible%20salesman%20preying%20on%20widows%20he%20located%20through%20obituary%20notices.%20His%20real-life%20daughter%2C%20Tatum%2C%20played%20a%20trash-talking%2C%20cigarette-smoking%20orphan%20who%20needs%20his%20help%20%E2%80%94%20and%20eventually%20helps%20redeem%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAlthough%20critics%20praised%20both%20actors%2C%20the%20little%20girl's%20brash%20performance%20overshadowed%20her%20father's%20and%20made%20her%20the%20youngest%20person%20in%20history%20to%20win%20a%20regular%20Academy%20Award.%20She%20was%2010%20when%20the%20award%20was%20presented%20in%201974.%20(Younger%20performers%20such%20as%20Shirley%20Temple%20have%20won%20special%20Oscars.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20elder%20O'Neal's%20next%20major%20film%20was%20Kubrick's%2018th%20century%20epic%20%26quot%3BBarry%20Lyndon%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20he%20played%20a%20poor%20Irish%20rogue%20who%20traveled%20Europe%20trying%20to%20pass%20himself%20off%20as%20an%20aristocrat.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFilming%20the%20three-hour%20movie%20was%20tedious%20work%2C%20however%2C%20and%20Kubrick's%20notorious%20perfectionism%20created%20a%20rift%20between%20him%20and%20the%20actor%20that%20never%20healed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Neal%20then%20reteamed%20with%20Tatum%20in%20Bogdanovich's%20early%20Hollywood%20comedy%20%26quot%3BNickelodeon%26quot%3B%20(1976).%20But%20the%20film%20was%20a%20flop%20and%20they%20never%20worked%20together%20again.%20An%20attempt%20to%20capitalize%20on%20his%20%26quot%3BLove%20Story%26quot%3B%20character%2C%20Oliver%20Barrett%2C%20with%20the%20sequel%20%26quot%3BOliver's%20Story%26quot%3B%20(1978)%20resulted%20in%20another%20flop.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFather%20and%20daughter%20drifted%20apart%20as%20Tatum%20O'Neal%20grew%20older%2C%20with%20the%20elder%20actor%20learning%20about%20his%20daughter's%20marriage%20to%20tennis%20great%20John%20McEnroe%20by%20a%20belated%20telegram%2C%20Ryan%20O'Neal%20wrote%20in%20a%202012%20book%20about%20his%20relationship%20with%20Fawcett.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BA%20door%20inside%20me%20locked%20the%20morning%20the%20telegram%20came%2C%20and%20I%20am%20still%20blindly%20searching%20for%20the%20key%20to%20open%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Neal%20wrote%20in%20%26quot%3BBoth%20of%20Us.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Neal's%20career%20cooled%20further%20in%20the%201980s%20with%20the%20emerald%20heist%20drama%20%26quot%3BGreen%20Ice%26quot%3B%20(1981)%20and%20the%201984%20comedy%20%26quot%3BIrreconcilable%20Differences%2C%26quot%3B%20in%20which%20he%20played%20a%20busy%20father%20in%20an%20unhappy%20marriage%20whose%20daughter%2C%20played%20by%209-year-old%20Drew%20Barrymore%2C%20tries%20to%20divorce%20her%20parents.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20decade%20was%20also%20a%20low-point%20in%20O'Neal's%20personal%20life.%20His%20son%20Griffin%20faced%20numerous%20brushes%20with%20the%20law%2C%20including%20a%201986%20boating%20accident%20that%20killed%20Gian-Carlo%20Coppola%2C%2023%2C%20son%20of%20movie%20director%20Francis%20Ford%20Coppola%20in%20Maryland.%20Griffin%20O'Neal%20was%20convicted%20of%20negligently%20and%20recklessly%20operating%20a%20boat%2C%20received%20a%20community%20service%20sentence%20and%20later%20served%20a%20brief%20stint%20in%20jail%20as%20a%20result.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20his%20Hollywood%20status%20diminishing%2C%20Ryan%20O'Neal%20began%20appearing%20in%20TV%20movies%20and%20eventually%20returned%20to%20series%20television%20opposite%20then-lover%20Fawcett%20with%20the%201991%20sitcom%20%26quot%3BGood%20Sports%2C%26quot%3B%20but%20the%20show%20ran%20only%20one%20season.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBoth%20acknowledged%20the%20work%20put%20a%20strain%20on%20their%20relationship.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20get%20into%20fights%2C%26quot%3B%20O'Neal%20said%20in%201991.%20%26quot%3BShe's%20tough.%20She%20expects%20to%20be%20treated%20well.%20On%20a%20set%20that%20can%20get%20lost%20when%20you're%20trying%20to%20create%20a%20moment%20and%20you're%20fighting%20the%20clock.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EO'Neal%20began%20accepting%20more%20supporting%20roles%20with%20the%201989%20film%20%26quot%3BChances%20Are.%26quot%3B%20He%20began%20a%20second%20career%20as%20a%20character%20actor%2C%20playing%20a%20husband%20who%20hires%20a%20hitman%20to%20kill%20his%20wife%20in%20%26quot%3BFaithful%26quot%3B%20(1996)%20and%20a%20mysterious%20tycoon%20in%20the%20blackmail%20comedy%20%26quot%3BZero%20Effect%26