%22_blank%5C%22%3Efighting%20the%20unionization%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20its%20U.S.%20stores.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20letter%20to%20Lynne%20Fox%2C%20the%20president%20of%20the%20Workers%20United%20union%2C%20Starbucks%20Chief%20Partner%20Officer%20Sara%20Kelly%20said%20the%20current%20bargaining%20impasse%20between%20the%20two%20sides%20%26quot%3Bshould%20not%20be%20acceptable%20to%20either%20of%20us.%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20asked%20to%20restart%20bargaining%20in%20January.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe%20will%20set%20as%20an%20ambition%20and%20hopeful%20goal%20the%20completion%20of%20bargaining%20and%20the%20ratification%20of%20contracts%20in%202024%2C%26quot%3B%20Kelly%20wrote%20in%20the%20letter.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20statement%20distributed%20by%20Workers%20United%2C%20Fox%20said%20she%20is%20reviewing%20the%20letter%20and%20will%20respond.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWe've%20never%20said%20no%20to%20meeting%20with%20Starbucks.%20Anything%20that%20moves%20bargaining%20forward%20in%20a%20positive%20way%20is%20most%20welcome%2C%26quot%3B%20Fox%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20United%20said%20the%20last%20bargaining%20session%20between%20the%20two%20sides%20was%20May%2023.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESaturday%20marks%20the%20two-year%20anniversary%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstarbucks-workers-in-buffalo-union-vote-results-2021-12%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Ea%20Starbucks%20store%20in%20Buffalo%2C%20New%20York%2C%3C%2Fa%3E%20voting%20to%20unionize.%20It%20was%20the%20first%20company-owned%20store%20to%20join%20a%20union%20in%20more%20than%20three%20decades.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESince%20then%2C%20at%20least%20370%20company-owned%20U.S.%20Starbucks%20stores%20have%20voted%20to%20unionize%2C%20according%20to%20the%20National%20Labor%20Relations%20Board.%20There%20are%20about%209%2C600%20company-owned%20Starbucks%20stores%20in%20the%20U.S.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWorkers%20at%2019%20U.S.%20Starbucks%20stores%20have%20filed%20petitions%20with%20the%20NLRB%2