%20that%20Hamby%20plans%20to%20negotiate%20with%20other%20states%20from%20his%20powerful%20position.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJohn%20Brooks%20Hamby%20was%209%20years%20old%20the%20last%20time%20a%20group%20of%20Western%20states%20renegotiated%20how%20they%20share%20the%20dwindling%20Colorado%20River.%20When%20the%20high-stakes%20talks%20concluded%20two%20years%20later%2C%20in%202007%2C%20with%20a%20round%20of%20painful%20cuts%2C%20he%20hadn't%20reached%20high%20school.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20this%20June%20an%20audience%20of%20water%20policy%20experts%20listened%20with%20rapt%20attention%20as%20Hamby%2C%20now%2027%2C%20recited%20lessons%20from%20those%20deliberations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamby%2C%20California's%20boyish-looking%20representative%20on%20issues%20concerning%20the%20river%2C%20sat%20shoulder-to-shoulder%20with%20the%20other%20states'%20powerful%20water%20managers%2C%20many%20of%20whom%20have%20decades%20of%20experience%2C%20an%20almost%20uncomfortable%20sight%20given%20their%20latest%20brawl%20over%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fwater-california-colorado-farmers-fear-drought-climate-change-biden-funding-2023-3%5C%22%3Ebeleaguered%20Colorado%20River%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20group%20had%20gathered%20in%20a%20mock%20courtroom%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Colorado%20Law%20School%20to%20discuss%20water%20law%20and%20to%20field%20questions%20about%20their%20negotiations%20over%20shortages%20that%20have%20prompted%20some%20cities%20to%20restrict%20growth%20and%20farmers%20to%20fallow%20fields.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20moderator%20asked%20whether%20states%20would%20allow%20Native%20American%20tribes%20in%20the%20basin%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Fseries%2Fwaiting-for-water%5C%22%3Ewho%20have%20often%20been%20denied%20the%20water%3C%2Fa%3E%20they%20were%20guaranteed%20by%20treaties%20and%20court%20rulings%2C%20to%20have%20an%20equal%20say%20in%20these%20decisions%2C%20referencing%20a%20question%20posed%20earlier%20by%20the%20governor%20of%20the%20Gila%20River%20Indian%20Community%2C%20a%20tribe%20in%20Arizona.%20Hamby%20jumped%20to%20offer%20a%20noncommittal%20answer%20about%20involving%20tribes%20in%20%26quot%3Beffective%20conversations%26quot%3B%20before%20pivoting%20to%20a%20discussion%20of%20how%2C%20during%20the%202007%20negotiations%2C%20smaller%20working%20groups%20had%20allowed%20the%20states%20and%20other%20water%20users%20to%20effectively%20iron%20out%20potential%20impasses.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20only%20other%20state%20delegate%20to%20respond%20endorsed%20Hamby's%20answer%2C%20a%20sign%20of%20how%20quickly%20he%20has%20risen%20to%20the%20top%20of%20the%20river's%20ranks.%20Hamby%20%E2%80%94%20who%20goes%20by%20J.B.%20%E2%80%94%20is%20the%20youngest%20of%20the%20Colorado%20River's%20%26quot%3Bwater%20buffaloes%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fcalifornia-western-states-disagree-colorado-river-cuts-proposal-borrowed-water-2023-2%5C%22%3Ewater%20managers%20who%20set%20policy%3C%2Fa%3E%20are%20known.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20his%20counterparts%20from%20the%20other%20basin%20states%20%E2%80%94%20Arizona%2C%20Colorado%2C%20Nevada%2C%20New%20Mexico%2C%20Utah%20and%20Wyoming%20%E2%80%94%20worked%20their%20way%20through%20water%20agencies%20or%20weathered%20the%20shifting%20politics%20of%20various%20governors%2C%20Hamby's%20ascent%20was%20swift.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20three-year%20span%2C%20he%20rose%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.desertsun.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2Felections%2F2020%2F11%2F04%2Fiid-board-shaken-up-but-incumbents-holding-coachella-valley%2F6166252002%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20recent%20Stanford%20University%20graduate%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20with%20a%20resume%20that%20touted%20little%20beyond%20a%20history%20degree%20and%20internships%20with%20Uber%20and%20a%20senator%2C%20to%20vice%20president%20of%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ffarming-families-california-use-more-water-than-some-states-2023-11%5C%22%3EImperial%20Irrigation%20District%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0board%20and%20chair%20of%20the%20Colorado%20River%20Board%20of%20California.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20former%20post%20gave%20him%20sway%20over%20the%20single%20largest%20user%20of%20Colorado%20River%20water%2C%20and%20the%20latter%20made%20him%20California's%20interstate%20negotiator%20for%20issues%20affecting%20the%20river%20basin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ECombined%2C%20these%20roles%20position%20Hamby%20as%20arguably%20the%20most%20powerful%20person%20involved%20in%20talks%20on%20the%20future%20of%20the%20Colorado%20River%2C%20a%20waterway%20that%20is%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fpacinst.org%2Fmanaging-the-unmeasured-colorado-river%2F%5C%22%3Erelied%20upon%20by%20an%20estimated%2035%20million%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20supports%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fbusinessforwater.org%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2016%2F12%2FPTF-Final-121814.pdf%5C%22%3E%241.4%20trillion%20worth%20of%20commerce%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThey%20also%20place%20him%20at%20the%20center%20of%20the%20river's%20most%20consequential%20moment%20since%20midcentury%2C%20when%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.usbr.gov%2Flc%2Fphoenix%2FAZ100%2F1960%2Fsupreme_court_AZ_vs_CA.html%5C%22%3EArizona%20and%20California%20went%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20fight%20over%20the%20amount%20of%20water%20they%20were%20allocated.%20Now%20the%20river's%20users%20must%20agree%20to%20dramatic%20cuts%2C%20as%20the%20river%20has%20been%20diminished%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.npr.org%2F2022%2F02%2F14%2F1080302434%2Fstudy-finds-western-megadrought-is-the-worst-in-1-200-years%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%20and%20drought%3C%2Fa%3E.%20It's%20a%20task%20that%20demands%20Hamby%20both%20protect%20California's%20long-standing%20water%20rights%20and%20lead%20all%20seven%20basin%20states%20to%20collaborate%20on%20a%20resolution%2C%20even%20though%20they'll%20all%20have%20to%20give%20ground.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamby%20holds%20the%20trump%20card.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fus-declares-first-colorado-river-shortage-arizona-nevada-water-cuts-2021-8%5C%22%3EThe%20Law%20of%20the%20River%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20the%20compacts%2C%20laws%20and%20court%20rulings%20that%20govern%20how%20the%20river%20is%20allocated%20%E2%80%94%20reflects%20a%20time%20when%20water%20use%20was%20encouraged%20to%20bring%20settlers%20west.%20And%20court%20decisions%20have%20favored%20users%20with%20senior%20priority%20rights%2C%20meaning%20those%20who%20were%20first%20to%20plant%20stakes%20along%20the%20river%2C%20file%20claims%20in%20county%20recorders'%20offices%20and%20prove%20their%20claims%20by%20taking%20water%20before%20federal%20and%20state%20water%20laws%20were%20codified.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222121%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20showing%20the%20bathtub%20ring%20where%20water%20used%20to%20sit%20fron%20the%20Colorado%20River%20water%20loss.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65664afcc58b6f84123b157c%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221413%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EWater%20loss%20has%20been%20revealing%20previously%20covered%20parts%20of%20the%20Colorado's%20rock%20formations.%3Cp%3EBloomberg%20Creative%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EThose%20with%20such%20rights%20are%20legally%20entitled%20to%20receive%20their%20share%20of%20the%20river%20before%20the%20next%20person%20or%20agency%20in%20line%20receives%20any.%20The%20Imperial%20Irrigation%20District%20holds%20some%20of%20the%20basin's%20oldest%20rights%2C%20dating%20back%20to%201901.%3Cp%3EHamby%20defends%20this%20system%2C%20which%20allows%20the%20Imperial%20Valley%20%E2%80%94%20home%20to%20only%20half%20of%20a%20percent%20of%20the%20river's%20users%2C%20Hamby%20included%20%E2%80%94%20to%20control%20about%20a%20quarter%20of%20the%20river's%20flow.%20That's%20more%20than%2010%20times%20southern%20Nevada's%20allocation%20and%20more%20than%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Famerican-southwest-mile-long-cracks-pumping-groundwater-2023-9%5C%22%3Eentire%20state%20of%20Arizona%20receives%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojects.propublica.org%2Fcalifornia-farmers-colorado-river%2F%5C%22%3Erecent%20ProPublica%20and%20Desert%20Sun%20analysis%20found%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%2020%20valley%20farming%20families%20use%20about%20387%20billion%20gallons%20of%20cheap%20water%20annually%2C%20most%20of%20it%20to%20grow%20cattle%20feed%2C%20and%20one%20family%20uses%20more%20water%20than%20the%20entire%20Las%20Vegas%20metropolitan%20area.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EEven%20so%2C%20Hamby%20can%20only%20go%20so%20far%20in%20dictating%20the%20terms%20of%20basinwide%20cuts.%20Strictly%20adhering%20to%20the%20century-old%20status%20quo%20would%20be%20catastrophic%2C%20as%20it%20would%20continue%20decades%20of%20overuse%20and%20could%20cut%20off%20the%20supply%20to%20millions%20of%20people%20in%20lower-priority%20cities%20and%20reservations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20if%20Hamby%20concedes%20too%20much%20to%20the%20other%20states%2C%20he%20risks%20costing%20California%20by%20upending%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Ftrump-signs-colorado-river-drought-plan-2019-4%5C%22%3Ehistorical%20agreements%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20put%20the%20Golden%20State%20at%20the%20front%20of%20the%20line.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20an%20IID%20director%2C%20he%20must%20protect%20the%20priority%20system%20preferred%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.propublica.org%2Farticle%2Fcalifornia-farm-families-gained-control-colorado-river%5C%22%3Efarmers%20who%20use%20most%20of%20the%20river%20and%20fear%20the%20cities%20eyeing%20their%20share%3C%2Fa%3E.%20As%20California's%20negotiator%2C%20he%20also%20represents%20cities%20like%20Los%20Angeles%20and%20San%20Diego%20as%20well%20as%20oft-overlooked%20tribes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWater%20is%20power.%20Water%20is%20control.%20So%20why%20would%20anyone%20want%20to%20give%20that%20up%2C%20to%20give%20it%20away%20to%20somebody%20else%3F%26quot%3B%20said%20Kyle%20Roerink%2C%20a%20Nevada%20environmentalist%20who%20runs%20the%20Great%20Basin%20Water%20Network%20and%20has%20joined%20unlikely%20coalitions%20with%20Hamby%20fighting%20the%20region's%20seemingly%20endless%20urban%20growth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20the%20basin%20states%20can't%20find%20agreement%2C%20then%20the%20Law%20of%20the%20River%20reigns%20supreme%2C%20Hamby%20told%20ProPublica%20and%20The%20Desert%20Sun%20earlier%20this%20year.%20%26quot%3BThat%20is%20the%20law%2C%20which%20everybody%20agreed%20to.%26quot%3B%20California%20is%20ready%20to%20compromise%20on%20cuts%2C%20he%20added%2C%20%26quot%3Bbut%20we%20need%20to%20see%20something%20come%20from%20the%20other%20states.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAn%20origin%20story%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22JB%20Hamby%20driving%20a%20car%20with%20his%20dry%20cleaning%20in%20the%20background.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6573753d0ec98e92f74dbaaf%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221993%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EHamby%20heading%20to%20a%20meeting%20for%20the%20water%20negotiations.%3Cp%3EJay%20Calderon%2FThe%20Desert%20Sun%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3EHamby%20grew%20up%20among%20the%20hot%20Imperial%20Valley%20farms%20and%20picked%20up%20the%20region's%20%26quot%3Bus%20against%20the%20world%26quot%3B%20mentality%20that%20flourishes%20alongside%20alfalfa%2C%20livestock%20and%20leafy%20greens.%20In%20California%2C%20dreams%20only%20go%20as%20far%20as%20water%20allows%2C%20and%20the%20valley's%20farmers%20live%20in%20constant%20fear%20that%20cities%20are%20lusting%20after%20the%20water%20that%20sustains%20the%20local%20economy.%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20Imperial%20Valley%2C%20locals'%20bona%20fides%20rest%20on%20how%20many%20generations%20back%20their%20family%20arrived%20in%20this%20hardscrabble%20desert.%20Hamby's%20great-grandfather%20%26quot%3Bcame%20here%20with%20%2410%20in%20his%20pocket%20on%20the%20back%20of%20a%20freight%20train%20from%20Big%20Spring%2C%20Texas%2C%26quot%3B%20as%20Hamby%20tells%20it%2C%20and%20worked%20as%20a%20ditch%20digger%20before%20starting%20a%20beekeeping%20business.%20His%20family%20has%20remained%20in%20the%20agriculture%20industry.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamby's%20father%20has%20held%20various%20gigs%2C%20from%20helping%20develop%20a%20farm%20in%20China%20(to%20the%20dismay%20of%20some%20Imperial%20Valley%20growers)%20to%20his%20current%20business%20growing%20seeds.%20And%20his%20mother%20worked%20on%20water%20issues%20from%20a%20different%20angle%2C%20serving%20as%20a%20county%20environmental%20health%20specialist%2C%20including%20focusing%20on%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.desertsun.com%2Fin-depth%2Fnews%2Fenvironment%2Fborder-pollution%2Fpoisoned-cities%2F2018%2F12%2F05%2Ftoxic-new-river-long-neglect-mexico-border-calexico-mexicali%2F1381599002%2F%5C%22%3Epollution%20that%20flowed%20through%20the%20valley%3C%2Fa%3E%20via%20the%20New%20River.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIf%20his%20family%20had%20a%20successful%20farm%20to%20pass%20on%2C%20Hamby%2C%20who%20was%20active%20in%204-H%20as%20a%20teenager%2C%20said%20he%20would've%20embraced%20that%20career%20path.%20%26quot%3BThere's%20been%20repeated%20struggle%2C%20and%20dreams%20will%20be%20built%20up%20and%20dashed%20and%20broken%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamby%20said%20of%20his%20family%20history.%20Instead%2C%20he%20looked%20for%20other%20ways%20to%20shape%20the%20valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDespite%20his%20agrarian%20upbringing%2C%20he%20had%20an%20origin%20story%20to%20launch%20him%20into%20conservative%20politics%2C%20if%20only%20he%20wanted%20that%20path.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%202014%2C%20Hamby%20was%20to%20give%20a%20speech%20at%20his%20graduation%20as%20the%20salutatorian%20of%20his%20Brawley%20Union%20High%20School%20class.%20But%20he%20had%20chosen%20to%20write%20an%20address%20about%20his%20Christian%20faith%2C%20to%20which%20school%20administrators%20objected%2C%20he%20said%2C%20forcing%20the%20teenager%20to%20rewrite%20it%20multiple%20times.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20the%20ceremony%2C%20he%20stepped%20to%20the%20lectern%2C%20the%20hot%20desert%20wind%20jostling%20his%20tassel%20and%20waving%20a%20line%20of%20American%20flags%20at%20his%20back.%20%26quot%3BCongratulations%2C%20class%20of%202014%2C%26quot%3B%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3D7BpCektnHt8%5C%22%3EHamby%20concluded%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20his%20words%20echoing%20over%20the%20sound%20system.%20%26quot%3BThank%20you%2C%20and%20may%20the%20God%20of%20the%20Bible%20bless%20you%2C%20each%20and%20every%20one%20of%20you%2C%20every%20day%20of%20the%20rest%20of%20your%20life.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20crowd%20cheered.%20Right-wing%20outlets%20including%20Fox%20News%20featured%20stories%20of%20a%20student%20standing%20up%20to%20what%20they%20saw%20as%20censors%2C%20dubbing%20him%20a%20%26quot%3Bred-blooded%2C%20Constitution-loving%20American.%26quot%3B%20He%20was%20interviewed%20on%20national%20television%20about%20his%20stand%20for%20Christian%20religious%20liberty.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20something%20kept%20pulling%20Hamby%20toward%20battles%20grounded%20less%20in%20identity%20politics%20and%20more%20in%20the%20day%20to%20day.%20Exactly%20how%20he%20came%20to%20combine%20water%20and%20politics%20wasn't%20entirely%20clear%20to%20him%20as%20he%20sat%20in%20a%20Mexican%20restaurant%20in%20the%20Imperial%20Valley%20town%20of%20El%20Centro%20earlier%20this%20year.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20the%20fight%20over%20his%20graduation%20speech%20was%20the%20beginning%20of%20his%20story%20in%20politics%2C%20he%20pushed%20back.%20%26quot%3BLives%20are%20very%20complicated%20and%20long%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20offered.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EFinding%20a%20cause%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22788%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Aerial%20shot%20of%20industrial%