d.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamby's%20message%20struck%20a%20chord.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20had%20studied%20recent%20successful%20political%20movements%3A%20populist%20Mexican%20President%20Andr%C3%A9s%20Manuel%20L%C3%B3pez%20Obrador's%20election%2C%20the%20Labour%20Party's%20landslide%201997%20win%20in%20Great%20Britain%20and%20the%20conservative%20pro-Brexit%20campaign%20in%202016.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20particularly%20inspired%20by%20the%20notorious%20big%20red%20bus%20that%20toured%20the%20United%20Kingdom%2C%20spreading%20the%20message%20that%20the%20country%20was%20spending%20huge%20sums%20to%20prop%20up%20the%20European%20Union%20%E2%80%94%20a%20persuasive%20argument%20that%20was%20a%20lie.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20took%20note%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthenevadaindependent.com%2Farticle%2Fwater-authority-board-votes-to-withdraw-remaining-water-rights-permits-for-pipeline-project%5C%22%3Eenvironmentalists%20using%20a%20giant%20mobile%20bucket%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20protest%20an%20attempt%20to%20move%20water%20from%20rural%20Nevada%20to%20Las%20Vegas.%20Hamby%20rented%20a%20flatbed%2C%20mounted%20a%20massive%20pipe%20on%20the%20back%20and%20had%20it%20driven%20around%20the%20Imperial%20Valley.%20The%20insinuation%3A%20This%20is%20how%20San%20Diego%20will%20buy%20and%20siphon%20off%20your%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPeople%20immediately%20got%20it%2C%20especially%20when%20you%20had%20a%2030-%2C%2040-foot%20pipe%20marauding%20around%20the%20area%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamby%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20vowed%20to%20hold%20a%20public%20referendum%20before%20any%20more%20Colorado%20River%20water%20was%20moved%20out%20of%20the%20valley.%20Hamby%20later%20led%20the%20charge%20to%20secure%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.desertsun.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fenvironment%2F2022%2F11%2F30%2Fiid-approves-possible-250-million-salton-sea-deal-with-feds-state%2F69687744007%2F%5C%22%3E%24250%20million%20in%20federal%20funds%3C%2Fa%3E%20if%20the%20irrigation%20district%20temporarily%20cut%20its%20use%20of%20river%20water%2C%20despite%20an%20outcry%20from%20farmers%20and%20environmental%20groups%20who%20only%20had%2024%20hours%20to%20review%20the%20plan%20before%20the%20board%20voted%20on%20it.%20No%20referendum%20has%20been%20held.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222793%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20photo%20of%20JB%20Hamby%20at%20the%20head%20of%20an%20empty%20conference%20table%20with%20an%20American%20flag%20behind%20him.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6573746b58e7c0c29a2b3db3%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222095%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJB%20Hamby%20is%20negotiating%20with%20delegates%20from%20states%20across%20the%20Southwest.%3Cp%3ECredit%3AJay%20Calderon%2FThe%20Desert%20Sun%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EAsked%20if%20he%20had%20broken%20his%20campaign%20promise%2C%20Hamby%20said%20that%20he%20is%20working%20to%20enshrine%20public%20input%20in%20district%20policy%20and%20that%20%26quot%3Bwe're%20not%20moving%20water%20to%20any%20other%20places.%20We're%20maintaining%20it%20in%20the%20system%20to%20be%20able%20to%20protect%20our%20sole%20source%20and%20supply.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20also%20made%20stylistic%20changes%20as%20he%20entered%20the%20political%20arena.%20He%20started%20going%20by%20J.B.%20because%20it%20sounds%20more%20%26quot%3Biconic%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20told%20a%20podcaster%2C%20and%20because%20potential%20voters%20were%20getting%20confused%20by%20the%20name%20Brooks%2C%20he%20told%20ProPublica%20and%20The%20Desert%20Sun.%20And%20he%20refined%20his%20look.%20He's%20clean-shaven%20and%20sports%20a%20high%20and%20tight%20haircut.%20His%20wardrobe%20could%20be%20described%20as%20%26quot%3Bcorporate%20outing%20meets%20Western%20wear%2C%26quot%3B%20often%20including%20a%20turquoise%20bolo%20tie%20and%20the%20IID%20crest%2C%20which%20features%20a%20crown%20adorning%20a%20shield%2C%20pinned%20to%20his%20lapel.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDuring%20his%20campaign%2C%20Hamby%20faced%20questions%20about%20his%20inexperience%20and%20choice%20to%20run%20in%20a%20district%20other%20than%20the%20one%20where%20he%20was%20raised.%20%26quot%3BJB%20is%20still%20a%20KID.%20JB%20needs%20a%20JOB.%20DON'T%20give%20him%20your%20VOTE.%20IID%20DIRECTOR%20should%20not%20be%20one's%20first%20JOB%20out%20of%20college%2C%26quot%3B%20one%20constituent%20commented%20online%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ivpressonline.com%2Fnews%2Flocal%2Fhigh-school-project-resurfaces-as-a-political-weapon%2Farticle_4b5e6c7c-f711-11ea-919a-d7fdf6221ce4.html%5C%22%3Eaccording%20to%20the%20Imperial%20Valley%20Press%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20a%20local%20newspaper%20that%20covered%20the%20race.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EStill%2C%20Hamby%20was%20the%20top%20vote-getter%20in%20the%20primary%2C%20beating%20an%20incumbent%20who%20cast%20the%20deciding%20vote%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.watereducation.org%2Faquapedia%2Fquantification-settlement-agreement%5C%22%3Ea%20controversial%202003%20agreement%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20transferred%20a%20portion%20of%20the%20valley's%20water%20to%20cities%20to%20help%20get%20California%20back%20within%20its%20allotment.%20Many%20of%20the%20valley's%20large%2C%20wealthy%20farming%20families%20supported%20Hamby's%20campaign%2C%20which%20brought%20in%20more%20than%20%24100%2C000%2C%20including%20loans%20from%20his%20father's%20company.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamby%20garnered%20nearly%20two-thirds%20of%20the%20general%20election%20vote.%20He%20had%20a%20mandate%20to%20defend%20the%20valley's%20water%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamby's%20time%20on%20the%20board%20got%20off%20to%20a%20combative%20start.%20While%20waiting%20to%20be%20seated%2C%20he%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcalexicochronicle.com%2F2020%2F11%2F30%2Fiid-labor-agreement-to-be-decided-dec-1%2F%5C%22%3Eshowed%20up%20at%20board%20meetings%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20publicly%20calling%20on%20members%20to%20avoid%20making%20important%20decisions%20until%20the%20new%20members%20were%20seated.%20He%20and%20another%20newly%20elected%20director%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.desertsun.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fenvironment%2F2020%2F12%2F10%2Fimperial-irrigation-board-seated-amid-tensions-over-labor-contract%2F6472202002%2F%5C%22%3Eskipped%20the%20district's%20official%20swearing-in%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20held%20their%20own%20due%20to%20a%20disagreement%20over%20who%20could%20attend%20amid%20COVID-19%20restrictions.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20outgoing%20board%20signed%20a%20sweeping%20project%20labor%20agreement%20with%20Southern%20California%20unions%20days%20before%20Hamby%20took%20office%2C%20he%20engineered%20a%20strategy%20to%20rip%20it%20up%20by%20declaring%20that%20the%20motion%20to%20approve%20it%20was%20ambiguous%20and%20voting%20to%20nullify%20it.%20That%20move%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.desertsun.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fpolitics%2F2021%2F05%2F13%2Fimperial-irrigation-district-directors-fighting-one-another-court%2F7294914002%2F%5C%22%3Eled%20to%20litigation%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20which%20was%20resolved%20when%20the%20district%20accepted%20a%20modified%20agreement.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOver%20time%2C%20as%20he%20confronted%20problems%20that%20would%20take%20collaboration%20to%20solve%2C%20Hamby's%20tone%20changed.%20The%20board%2C%20which%20has%20a%20history%20of%20dysfunction%2C%20confronted%20issues%20ranging%20from%20mandatory%20water%20conservation%20that%20is%20shrinking%20the%20Salton%20Sea%20%E2%80%94%20a%20terminal%20lake%20fed%20by%20irrigation%20runoff%20that%20is%20now%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hcn.org%2Fissues%2F53.1%2Fsouth-water-will-california-finally-fulfill-its-promise-to-fix-the-salton-sea%5C%22%3Eexposing%20communities%20to%20toxic%20dust%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20water%20levels%20fall%20and%20uncover%20the%20lakebed%20%E2%80%94%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.desertsun.com%2Fin-depth%2Ftech%2Fscience%2Fenergy%2F2018%2F08%2F01%2Fcalifornia-desert-farm-baron-builds-water-and-energy-empire%2F636894002%2F%5C%22%3Ea%20powerful%20farmer%3C%2Fa%3E%20who%20has%20been%20battling%20in%20court%20to%20break%20the%20irrigation%20district's%20control%20over%20water.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20Hamby's%20colleagues%2C%20including%20fellow%20Director%20Javier%20Gonzalez%2C%20praised%20the%20young%20director's%20leadership.%20%26quot%3BHe's%20a%20hard%20worker%2C%26quot%3B%20Gonzalez%20said.%20%26quot%3BHe%20gets%20things%20done.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20rewards%20of%20the%20job%20are%20less%20financial%20and%20more%20the%20ability%20to%20pursue%20policy%20goals.%20The%20irrigation%20district's%20directors%20make%20around%20%2450%2C000%20annually.%20Hamby%20drives%20an%20aging%20Toyota%20Prius%20and%20says%20he%20lives%20in%20a%20%26quot%3Bbachelor%20apartment.%26quot%3B%20But%20even%20with%20his%20work%20ethic%2C%20there%20were%20limits%20to%20how%20much%20Hamby%20could%20deliver%20on%20his%20campaign%20promises%20to%20keep%20the%20district's%20water%20in%20the%20Imperial%20Valley.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ETo%20do%20that%2C%20he%20needed%20to%20be%20at%20the%20table%20with%20the%20basin's%20water%20buffaloes.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EAt%20the%20head%20of%20the%20table%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%22966%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Gavin%20Newsom%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65664d6bfd6200867dd05310%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22724%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EGovernor%20Gavin%20Newsom%20of%20California.%3Cp%3EAP%20Photo%2FRich%20Pedroncelli%2CFile%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EPower%20in%20the%20Colorado%20River%20Basin%20lies%20largely%20with%20the%20seven%20states%20and%20their%20designated%20representatives%20now%20haggling%20over%20cuts%20to%20water%20allocations.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcrb.ca.gov%2F%5C%22%3EColorado%20River%20Board%20of%20California%3C%2Fa%3E%20is%20the%20state's%20representative.%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fgavin-newsom-career-timeline%5C%22%3EGov.%20Gavin%20Newsom%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0appointed%20Hamby%20to%20the%20board%20a%20few%20months%20after%20he%20was%20sworn%20in%20at%20the%20irrigation%20district.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ELess%20than%20two%20years%20later%2C%20the%20chair%2C%20who%20acts%20as%20the%20state's%20negotiator%2C%20unexpectedly%20announced%20he%20wouldn't%20seek%20reelection.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20board%20is%20split%20between%20representatives%20of%20rural%20water%20districts%20that%20largely%20serve%20farmers%20and%20urban%20water%20districts%20serving%20Los%20Angeles%2C%20San%20Diego%20and%20other%20cities.%20A%20member%20of%20the%20San%20Diego%20County%20Water%20Authority%20board%20emerged%20as%20the%20cities'%20candidate%20for%20chair%2C%20with%20Hamby%20as%20the%20preference%20of%20the%20rural%20irrigation%20districts.%20Neither%20candidate%20had%20enough%20votes%20to%20win%2C%20and%20some%20of%20Hamby's%20earlier%20brash%20remarks%20left%20an%20older%20water%20manager%20feeling%20uneasy%20about%20voting%20for%20him.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EGlen%20Peterson%2C%20who%20was%20then%20the%20board's%20representative%20from%20the%20Metropolitan%20Water%20District%20of%20Southern%20California%2C%20which%20serves%2019%20million%20people%2C%20was%20considering%20supporting%20Hamby%20but%20%26quot%3Bhad%20concerns%26quot%3B%20about%20his%20public%20statements.%20After%20a%20frank%20conversation%20between%20the%20two%20and%20some%20maneuvering%20with%20other%20board%20members%2C%20the%20votes%20shifted.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI%20think%20he's%20a%20wonderful%20kid.%20And%20he's%20really%20smart%20and%2C%20for%20his%20age%2C%20he%20is%20extremely%20mature%2C%26quot%3B%20Peterson%20said.%20%26quot%3BI%20mean%2C%20this%20guy%20probably%20sat%20at%20the%20big%20people's%20table%20when%20he%20was%20a%20teenager.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHamby%20was%20elected%20the%20new%20chair%2C%20overseeing%20California's%20negotiations%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20basin%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTraditionally%2C%20it's%20been%2C%20'You%20hold%20the%20role%20and%20then%20you%20die%20in%20it%2C'%26quot%3B%20Hamby%20explained.%20%26quot%3BIID's%20had%20three%20people%20hold%20the%20position%20before.%20The%20previous%20three%20died%20in%20the%20role.%26quot%3B%20(The%20chair%20of%20the%20board%20now%20serves%20four-year%20terms%2C%20but%20there%20is%20no%20limit%20on%20the%20number%20of%20terms.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20asked%20what%20happens%20next%20on%20the%20river%2C%20where%20he%20would've%20once%20brought%20rhetorical%20fire%20and%20brimstone%2C%20he%20now%20offers%20coded%20responses.%20%26quot%3BI%20need%20to%20develop%20truly%20consensus-based%20approaches%20to%20develop%20a%20new%20set%20of%20operating%20guidelines%20and%20standards%20that%20everybody%20can%20agree%20on%2C%20because%20there's%20necessity%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3ECharting%20the%20river's%20future%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224657%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22An%20aerial%20photo%20taken%20of%20the%20Colorado%20river.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F65664b7afe5bc6545ebd1475%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223493%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20Colorado%20River%20flow.%3Cp%3EGeorge%20Rose%2FContributor%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EWith%20aggressive%20conservation%20efforts%20already%20underway%20in%20some%20parts%20of%20the%20Colorado%20River%20Basin%2C%20policymakers%20are%20realizing%20that%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fprojects.propublica.org%2Fturf-wars%2F%5C%22%3Eripping%20out%20lawns%20and%20installing%20low-flow%20toilets%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20metropolitan%20areas%20won't%20be%20enough%20to%20save%20the%20river.%20Agriculture%20uses%20an%20estimated%20three-quarters%20or%20more%20of%20the%20river%2C%20meaning%20any%20solution%20must%20include%20cuts%20to%20farmers'%20allocations%20and%20a%20rethinking%20of%20the%20long-protected%20priority%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThat%20puts%20IID%20and%20California%2C%20with%20their%20senior%20water%20rights%2C%20at%20odds%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20basin.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20January%202023%2C%20facing%20a%20federal%20deadline%20to%20come%20up%20with%20a%20plan%20to%20cut%20water%20use%2C%20the%20other%20six%20basin%20states%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.reviewjournal.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-government%2Fnevada%2Fcalifornia-lags-as-other-colorado-river-states-agree-on-water-cuts-2720878%2F%5C%22%3Ereleased%20a%20joint%20letter%3C%2Fa%3E%20detailing%20their%20idea%20to%20conserve%20water.%20California%2C%20which%20potentially%20faced%20the%20heaviest%20cuts%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fapnews.com%2Farticle%2Fpolitics-colorado-river-california-climate-and-environment-2ef8db8071dd911e84e7f345583206ed%5C%22%3Ewas%20the%20only%20state%20not%20to%20sign%20onto%20the%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BCompromise%20really%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Farizona-water-goes-saudi-firm-states-fight-over-colorado-river-2023-7%5C%22%3Ewasn't%20in%20the%20air%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20the%20time%2C%26quot%3B%20Hamby%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20day%20later%2C%20the%20Colorado%20River%20Board%20of%20California%2C%20with%20Hamby%20at%20the%20helm%2C%20rushed%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.desertsun.com%2Fstory%2Fnews%2Fenvironment%2F2023%2F02%2F01%2Fcalifornia-fires-back-at-other-states-with-its-own-colorado-river-plan%2F69861076007%2F%5C%22%3Erelease%20its%20own%20plan%3C%2Fa%3E.%20The%20board%20flexed%20California's%20water%20rights%2C%20arguing%20in%20a%20statement%20that%20the%20other%20states'%20proposal%20%26quot%3Bconflicts%20with%20the%20existing%20Law%20of%20the%20River%26quot%3B%20and%20undermines%20the%20priority%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20ensuing%20weeks%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.latimes.com%2Fenvironment%2Fstory%2F2023-02-09%2Fevaporation-takes-center-stage-in-colorado-river-crisis%5C%22%3EHamby%20made%20it%20known%3C%2Fa%3E%20that%20the%20other%20states'%20methodology%20for%20saving%20water%2C%20which%20put%20California%20at%20a%20disadvantage%2C%20was%20untenable.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThat%20moment%20looked%20like%20the%20example%20of%20him%20digging%20in%20his%20heels%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Elizabeth%20Koebele%2C%20an%20associate%20professor%20of%20political%20science%20at%20the%20University%20of%20Nevada%2C%20Reno%20who%20studies%20the%20river's%20governance.%20She%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWe%20did%20see%20the%20power%20of%20California%20and%20the%20role%20that%20their%20legal%20position%20plays%20on%20the%20river.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBut%20unless%20Hamby%20were%20willing%20to%20exercise%20the%20nuclear%20option%20and%20test%20the%20strength%20of%20California's%20legal%20position%20in%20court%2C%20he'd%20have%20to%20give%20up%20something%20to%20protect%20water%20rights%20in%20the%20state.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHe%20embraced%20diplomacy%2C%20writing%20thank-you%20notes%20to%20other%20states'%20representatives%20and%20beginning%20to%20broker%20a%20new%20plan%20among%20the%20Lower%20Basin%20states%3A%20California%2C%20Arizona%20and%20Nevada.%20In%20it%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.ca.gov%2F2023%2F05%2F22%2Farizona-california-and-nevada-governors-announce-lower-basin-plan-to-protect-colorado-river%2F%5C%22%3Ethey%20agreed%20to%20apportion%20short-term%20cuts%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20importantly%2C%20without%20changing%20the%20priority%20system%20or%20water%20accounting%20in%20the%20long%20run%20%E2%80%94%20until%20a%20new%20set%20of%20rules%20and%20agreements%20could%20be%20hammered%20out.%20That%20new%20plan%20is%20due%20by%20the%20end%20of%202026.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%223000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Delegates%20sit%20at%20a%20long%20podium%20with%20a%20crest%20behind%20them.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F657374d37a3c8094d5db3ed0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcapti