ps%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F03215407%2FScreenshot-2022-02-03-at-9.53.14-PM.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20victory%20lap%20following%20the%20assembly%20elections%20over.%20It%20was%20time%20to%20get%20down%20to%20the%20acrimonious%20business%20of%20taking%20on%20vociferous%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%20critic%2C%20Trinamool%20Congress%20(TMC)%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%2C%20by%20expelling%20her%20from%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20strategically%20on%20a%20Friday%20afternoon%20with%20the%20Treasury%20Benches%20hoping%20the%20furore%20will%20die%20out%20over%20the%20weekend.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20Moitra%20says%20she%20has%20other%20plans.%20%E2%80%9CI%20am%2049%20years%20old.%20I%20will%20fight%20you%20for%20the%20next%2030%20years%2C%20inside%20parliament%2C%20outside%20parliament%2C%20in%20the%20gutters%2C%20you%20on%20the%20streets.%20I%20will%20see%20the%20end%20of%20you%2C%20do%20not%20wonder%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20said%2C%20in%20the%20presence%20of%20senior%20parliamentarians%20like%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20Farooq%20Abdullah%2C%20and%20her%20own%20party%20MPs%20standing%20behind%20her.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20optics%20of%20it%20all%20were%20clear%20in%20the%20House.%20The%20mighty%20BJP%20issued%20a%20whip%20to%20its%20303%20MPs%20to%20be%20present%20to%20expel%20one%20member%20of%20parliament%20based%20on%20the%20recommendations%20of%20the%20Ethics%20committee.%20The%20acrimony%20began%20with%20the%20tabling%20of%20the%20report%20that%20was%20listed%20in%20the%20business%20of%20the%20House%20on%20Monday%20itself%20but%20not%20laid%20then%20as%20the%20BJP%20did%20not%20want%20the%20limelight%20to%20shift%20away%20from%20%E2%80%9CPrime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20winning%20the%20three%20assembly%20polls%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fmahua-moitra-tmc-lok-sabha-ethic-panel-expel-adjourn%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Kangaroo%20Court%2C%20Modi%20Govt%20Can%E2%80%99t%20Shut%20Me%20Up%E2%80%99%2C%20Says%20TMC%20MP%20Mahua%20Moitra%2C%20Expelled%20From%20Lok%20Sabha%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20extent%20of%20opposition%20unity%20was%20clearer%20outside.%20The%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20seen%20to%20be%20on%20shaky%20ground%20after%20the%20Congress%E2%80%99%20disastrous%20performance%20in%20the%20Assembly%20polls%2C%20rallied%20behind%20the%20TMC%20with%20members%20of%20the%20opposition%20appealing%20to%20Speaker%20Om%20Birla%20to%20let%20Moitra%20speak%20in%20the%20House.%20Sonia%20Gandhi%2C%20usually%20seen%20to%20be%20at%20the%20forefront%20of%20any%20gathering%2C%20conceded%20the%20space%20to%20Moitra.%20The%20TMC%2C%20which%20had%20initially%20been%20cool%20to%20its%20MP%20when%20the%20allegations%20first%20broke%2C%20made%20an%20impassioned%20plea%20to%20the%20Speaker%20in%20the%20House%20that%20Moitra%20be%20allowed%20to%20defend%20herself%20%E2%80%93%20an%20opportunity%20allegedly%20denied%20to%20her%20by%20the%20Ethics%20Committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EParty%20chief%20Mamata%20Banerjee%20on%20a%20visit%20to%20Kurseong%2C%20Darjeeling%2C%20told%20reporters%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20congratulate%20the%20INDIA%20alliance.%20They%20are%20united%20and%20fight%20back.%20Our%20party%20fully%20supports%20Mahua%E2%80%99s%20case.%20Mahua%20will%20win%20the%20battle%20and%20people%20will%20give%20a%20befitting%20reply%20to%20the%20BJP.%E2%80%9D%20On%20questions%20on%20how%20they%20fight%20this%20case%2C%20she%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CPolitically%20we%20will%20fight%20and%20people%20will%20fight%20and%20will%20give%20the%20justice.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EINDIA%20alliance%20rallies%20behind%20Moitra%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20BJP%2C%20La%E2%80%99affaire%20Moitra%20was%20a%20tit-for-tat%20moment%20against%20historic%20grievances%20the%20party%20held%20when%20six%20of%20its%20MPs%20were%20expelled%20from%20the%20House%20in%20the%202005%20cash-for-query%20scandal.%20Online%20portal%2C%20%3Cem%3ECobraPost%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20had%20done%20a%20sting%20operation%20against%20these%20MPs%20and%20caught%20them%20on%20camera%20accepting%20cash.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20allegation%20against%20Moitra%2C%20for%20which%20she%20was%20expelled%2C%20was%20that%20she%20shared%20her%20Lok%20sabha%20portal%20login%20and%20password%20details%20with%20Dubai-based%20business%20Darshan%20Hiranandani%2C%20who%20in%20turn%2C%20loaded%20a%20majority%20of%20the%20questions%20on%20her%20behalf%20in%20return%20for%20cash%20and%20gifts.%20The%20questions%20were%20majorly%20those%20in%20which%20the%20Hiranandani%20group%20had%20business%20interests%20that%20clashed%20with%20those%20of%20business%20tycoon%20Gautam%20Adani.%20The%20allegations%2C%20of%20what%20is%20being%20called%20the%20%E2%80%9Ccash-for-query%E2%80%9D%20scam%20by%20the%20BJP%2C%20were%20made%20by%20Moitra%E2%80%99s%20bete%20noire%2C%20Nishikant%20Dubey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20report%20was%20tabled%20at%20noon%20and%20a%20half-hour%20discussion%20was%20slated%20from%202%20pm%20to%20debate%20the%20report.%20TMC%20MP%20Sudip%20Bandopadhyaya%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20had%20to%20write%20a%20letter%20to%20the%20Speaker%20to%20be%20given%20a%20copy.%20The%20495-page%20report%20has%20been%20shared%20with%20the%20party%20now%20just%20as%20the%20House%20is%20reconvening%20and%20a%20version%20uploaded%20on%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20portal.%20I%20asked%20for%2048%20hours%20to%20study%20the%20report%20but%20we%20are%20expected%20to%20read%20the%20report%20and%20debate%20on%20it%20all%20within%20half%20an%20hour.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDefending%20this%2C%20parliamentary%20affairs%20minister%20Prahlad%20Joshi%20told%20reporters%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20operative%20part%20of%20the%20report%2C%20some%2020%20odd%20pages%2C%20were%20uploaded%20on%20the%20portal%20as%20parliament%20has%20now%20gone%20paperless.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInside%20the%20House%2C%20responding%20to%20allegations%20that%20no%20time%20had%20been%20given%20to%20members%20to%20read%20the%20495-page%20report%20and%20that%20Moitra%20was%20being%20expelled%20on%20the%20same%20day%20without%20a%20hearing%2C%20Joshi%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThen%20Speaker%20Somnath%20Chatterjee%20had%20given%20a%20ruling%20in%20a%20similar%20manner.%20He%20had%20said%20the%20MPs%20had%20been%20given%20an%20opportunity%20before%20the%20Pawan%20Bansal%20committee.%20They%20cant%20be%20allowed%20to%20speak%20in%20the%20House%20now.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202%20pm%20debate%20began%20with%20Birla%20taking%20the%20high%20moral%20ground.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20country%20looks%20up%20to%20us%20to%20set%20high%20parliamentary%20standards.%20Our%20behaviour%20should%20not%20be%20a%20blot%20on%20democratic%20principles%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBeginning%20the%20debate%2C%20Manish%20Tiwari%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThe%20whip%20should%20be%20withdrawn.%20We%20are%20sitting%20as%20a%20jury%20and%20it%20should%20be%20left%20to%20the%20conscience%20of%20the%20members.%20The%20member%20against%20whom%20allegations%20have%20been%20levelled%2C%20hasn%E2%80%99t%20been%20given%20an%20opportunity%20to%20be%20heard%20or%20cross%20examine%20those%20who%20made%20these%20allegations.%20As%20per%20the%20Ethics%20committee%20can%20recommend%20whether%20the%20person%20is%20innocent%20or%20guilty%20but%20it%20cannot%20recommend%20what%20punishment%20should%20be%20levied.%20That%20power%20rests%20with%20the%20House%20to%20decide%20the%20quantum%20of%20punishment.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBJP%20MP%20Heena%20Gavit%20countered%20the%20opposition.%20%E2%80%9CDarshan%20Hiranandani%20has%20said%20on%20affidavit%20that%20he%20gave%20her%20cash%20and%20jewellery.%20And%20the%20MP%20herself%20admitted%20that%20she%20gave%20her%20login%20ID%20and%20password%20to%20Hirnandani.%20This%20is%20clearly%20against%20the%20rules.%20Moreover%2C%20her%20credentials%20were%20used%20from%20five%20different%20places%20in%20one%20day%20including%20Delhi%2C%20Dubai%20and%20the%20US.%20This%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20parliamentary%20procedures%20and%20the%20image%20of%20India%E2%80%99s%20MPs%20has%20been%20tarnished%20in%20India%20and%20globally.%20It%20is%20wrong%20to%20say%20this%20is%20Draupadi%E2%80%99s%20%3Cem%3Echeerharan%3C%2Fem%3E.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETMC%20leader%20Kalyan%20Banerjee%20and%20Sudip%20Bandopadhyaya%E2%80%99s%20pleas%20that%20on%20behalf%20of%20the%20TMC%2C%20their%20speaker%20would%20be%20Moitra%20was%20turned%20down%20by%20the%20Speaker.%20Banerjee%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CA%20fair%20trial%20would%20be%20there%20if%20the%20affected%20person%20is%20being%20heard.%20We%20are%20acting%20as%20a%20quasi-judicial%20body.%20I%20am%20requesting%20that%20you%20allow%20her%20to%20speak.%20Hiranandani%E2%80%99s%20affidavit%20has%20been%20relied%20upon.%20He%20has%20not%20testified%20before%20the%20committee.%20No%20affidavit%20can%20be%20relied%20upon%20unless%20the%20person%20comes%20before%20the%20committee.%20The%20right%20to%20cross-examine%20has%20not%20been%20allowed.%20This%20has%20been%20established%20by%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20too.%20This%20is%20a%20violation%20of%20the%20principle%20of%20natural%20justice.%20Her%20right%20as%20protected%20under%20Article%2014%20of%20the%20Constitution%20has%20been%20violated.%C2%A0%20Besides%2C%20the%20rules%20don%E2%80%99t%20permit%2C%20the%20Constitution%20doesn%E2%80%99t%20permit%20her%20expulsion%20under%20Article%20102%20and%20the%2010%3Csup%3Eth%3C%2Fsup%3E%20Schedule%20of%20the%20Constitution.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EInterstingly%2C%20Janata%20Dal%20(United)%20MP%20and%20member%20of%20the%20Ethic%20Committee%20Giridhari%20Yadav%2C%20whom%20Moitra%20refers%20to%20as%20the%20Govinda%20for%20Draupadi%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CMy%20questions%20have%20always%20been%20asked%20by%20my%20PA%20and%20other%20staff.%20I%20don%E2%80%99t%20even%20know%20how%20to%20use%20a%20computer.%20This%20time%20I%20was%20so%20scared%20after%20seeing%20all%20this%20that%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20ask%20a%20single%20question.%E2%80%9D%20He%20said%20all%20MPs%20share%20their%20credentials%20with%20their%20staff%20and%20that%20Moitra%20was%20%E2%80%9Cbeing%20singled%20out%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETo%20which%20Birla%20warned%20him%2C%20%E2%80%9CAction%20can%20be%20taken%20against%20you%20if%20you%20say%20that%20you%20do%20not%20ask%20your%20own%20questions.%20This%20is%20very%20serious.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Committee%20also%20censured%20MP%20Danish%20Ali%20for%20violating%20the%20%E2%80%9Cconfidentiality%20clause%E2%80%9D%20and%20%E2%80%9Cinciting%20the%20public%20by%20cunningly%20twisting%20the%20deliberations%20of%20the%20committee%E2%80%9D.%20Ali%20told%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20take%20this%20censure%20as%20a%20badge%20of%20honour.%20When%20history%20is%20written%2C%20i%20will%20be%20remembered%20as%20someone%20who%20stood%20up%20for%20the%20honour%20of%20a%20woman%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20last%20word%2C%20however%2C%20went%20to%20Moitra%20who%20outside%20the%20House%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CThis%20is%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%20end.%20%3Cem%3EJab%20naash%20manush%20par%20chaata%20hai%20toh%20pehle%20vivek%20mar%20jaata%20hai%3C%2Fem%3E%20(When%20the%20end%20is%20near%2C%20man%20loses%20his%20morality%20first)%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702046946000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F02%2F03215407%2FScreenshot-2022-02-03-at-9.53.14-PM.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbeginning-of-the-end-will-fight-you-for-the-next-30-years-moitra-fires-at-bjp-after-expulsion%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20extent%20of%20opposition%20unity%20was%20clearer%20outside.%20The%20INDIA%20alliance%2C%20seen%20to%20be%20on%20shaky%20ground%20after%20the%20Assembly%20polls%2C%20rallied%20behind%20the%20TMC%20member%20appealing%20to%20Speaker%20to%20let%20her%20speak%20in%20the%20House.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fpolitics%2Fbeginning-of-the-end-will-fight-you-for-the-next-30-years-moitra-fires-at-bjp-after-expulsion%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Govt%20Refuses%20to%20Give%20Clarity%20on%20%E2%80%98One%20Nation%20One%20Election%E2%80%99%20Deadline%3B%20Congress%20MPs%20Seek%20Details%20on%20Committee%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16163914%2F2048px-BMC_Election_2012_-_Ink_mark_after_voting_6886404209.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Union%20government%20has%20refused%20to%20provide%20a%20clear%20answer%20to%20three%20Congress%20MPs%20on%20whether%20it%20has%20given%20a%20fixed%20deadline%20to%20the%20high-level%20committee%2C%20under%20former%20president%20Ram%20Nath%20Kovind%2C%20to%20submit%20its%20report%20on%20the%20implementation%20of%20the%20%E2%80%98one%20nation%20one%20election%E2%80%99%20theory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20starred%20question%20was%20jointly%20raised%20by%20Congress%20Lok%20Sabha%20MPs%20Adoor%20Prakash%2C%20Anto%20Antony%2C%20and%20Su.%20Thirunavukkarasar%20to%20the%20Union%20Ministry%20of%20Law%20and%20Justice.%20They%20also%20sought%20more%20details%20on%20the%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20theory%20of%20%E2%80%98one%20nation%20one%20election%E2%80%99%20has%20been%20advocated%20by%20leaders%20of%20the%20ruling%20dispensation%2C%20including%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%2C%20the%20government%20had%20remained%20tight-lipped%20about%20any%20move%20in%20that%20direction%20for%20quite%20a%20while.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20things%20began%20to%20move%20in%20that%20direction%20in%20August-end.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20the%20government%20described%20a%20meeting%20between%20Union%20home%20minister%20Amit%20Shah%20and%20Minister%20of%20State%20(Independent%20Charge)%20Arjun%20Ram%20Meghwal%20with%20Kovind%20at%20his%20residence%20at%20the%20end%20of%20August%20as%20%E2%80%98a%20courtesy%20call%E2%80%99%2C%20on%20September%201%2C%20it%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fgovt-working-on-logistics-modalities-for-panel-on-one-nation-one-election%2Farticleshow%2F103444062.cms%5C%22%3Enotified%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20committee%20led%20by%20the%20former%20president%20to%20look%20into%20the%20possibility%20of%20simultaneous%20parliamentary%20and%20assembly%20elections.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20notification%20on%20the%20formation%20of%20the%20eight-member%20committee%20drew%20media%20attention%2C%20particularly%20because%20it%20came%20just%20days%20before%20the%20Parliament%20was%20to%20be%20in%20a%20special%20session%20(between%20September%2018%20and%2022)%20with%20the%20government%20not%20announcing%20any%20particular%20agenda%20for%20it.%20It%20was%20also%20the%20time%20when%20the%20Election%20Commission%20of%20India%20was%20finalising%20the%20schedule%20for%20the%20assembly%20elections%20in%20five%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20government%E2%80%99s%20September%201%20notification%20said%20that%20aside%20from%20Kovind%2C%20the%20committee%20would%20have%20Shah%20too.%20Opposition%20leader%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20and%20former%20Congress%20leader%20Ghulam%20Nabi%20Azad%2C%20now%20seen%20close%20to%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%2C%20were%20also%20named%20as%20members.%20Former%20Finance%20Commission%20chairman%20N.K.%20Singh%2C%20senior%20advocate%20Harish%20Salve%2C%20former%20secretary%20general%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Subhash%20Kashyap%2C%20and%20former%20chief%20vigilance%20commissioner%20Sanjay%20Kothari%20were%20the%20other%20members.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20Chowdhury%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Feconomictimes.indiatimes.com%2Fnews%2Fpolitics-and-nation%2Fadhir-ranjan-chowdhury-declines-to-be-on-one-nation-one-election-panel-as-cong-attacks-modi-govt-move%2Farticleshow%2F103314580.cms%5C%22%3Erefused%20to%20be%20part%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20committee%2C%20saying%20that%20it%20was%20tailor-made%20to%20reach%20certain%20conclusions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20September%2023%2C%20Kovind%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiatoday.in%2Findia%2Fstory%2Fformer-president-ram-nath-kovind-first-meeting-high-level-panel-synchronised-polls-2439631-2023-09-23%5C%22%3Echaired%3C%2Fa%3E%20the%20committee%E2%80%99s%20first%20meeting%20in%20New%20Delhi%2C%20during%20which%20it%20decided%20to%20invite%20political%20parties%20and%20the%20Law%20Commission%20to%20seek%20their%20views%20on%20the%20subject.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Law%20Commission%2C%20on%20October%2023%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Flaw-commission-presents-roadmap-on-one-nation-one-election-to-ram-nath-kovind-led-panel%2Farticle67459227.ece%5C%22%3Esuggested%3C%2Fa%3E%20a%20roadmap%20to%20the%20Kovind%20committee%20on%20how%20to%20proceed%20on%20the%20matter.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20December%208%2C%20while%20replying%20to%20the%20queries%20put%20up%20by%20the%20Congress%20MPs%2C%20the%20law%20ministry%2C%20in%20a%20written%20reply%2C%20avoided%20answering%20whether%20any%20fixed%20term%20had%20been%20set%20for%20the%20committee%20to%20submit%20its%20report.%20Its%20written%20statement%20only%20gave%20the%20objectives%20of%20the%20committee%20and%20also%20justified%20its%20action%20by%20banking%20on%20the%20precedent%20of%20parliamentary%20and%20assembly%20polls%20%E2%80%9Cmostly%20held%20simultaneously%20from%201951-52%20to%201967%2C%20after%20which%20this%20cycle%20got%20broken%E2%80%9D.%20Due%20to%20elections%20being%20organised%20every%20one%20or%20two%20years%2C%20it%20leads%20to%20more%20expenditure%2C%20diversion%20of%20manpower%2C%20including%20security%20forces%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cdisruption%20of%20development%20work%E2%80%9D%2C%20it%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThese%20arguments%20have%20been%20publicly%20stated%20by%20the%20prime%20minister%2C%20too%2C%20even%20prior%20to%20forming%20the%20Kovind-led%20committee.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20statement%20in%20Parliament%2C%20the%20law%20ministry%20referred%20to%20the%20parliamentary%20standing%20committee%20on%20law%20and%20justice%20suggesting%20this%20theory%20in%202015%20and%20the%20Law%20Commission%20mooting%20the%20same%20in%202018.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20mandate%20of%20the%20commission%2C%20as%20per%20the%20reply%2C%20is%20not%20only%20to%20suggest%20amendment%20to%20the%20constitution%20to%20make%20the%20simultaneous%20elections%20possible%2C%20but%20also%20to%20set%20up%20a%20framework%20suggesting%20phases%20and%20the%20time%20frame%20for%20the%20synchronisation.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%2C%20however%2C%20had%20a%20line%20which%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Chigh%20level%20committee%20shall%20start%20functioning%20immediately%20and%20make%20recommendations%20at%20the%20earliest.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThough%20the%20committee%20is%20yet%20to%20submit%20its%20recommendations%2C%20on%20November%2021%2C%20Kovind%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.hindustantimes.com%2Findia-news%2Fpanel-chief-kovind-backs-one-nation-one-election-101700507961425.html%5C%22%3Esaid%3C%2Fa%3E%20he%20supported%20the%20idea%20of%20one%20nation%20one%20election%2C%20and%20asked%20all%20political%20parties%20to%20support%20it%20in%20%E2%80%9Cnational%20interest%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702045149000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F01%2F16163914%2F2048px-BMC_Election_2012_-_Ink_mark_after_voting_6886404209.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fgovt-refuses-to-give-clarity-on-one-nation-one-election-deadline-congress-mps-seek-details-on-committee%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Though%20the%20theory%20of%20'one%20nation%20one%20election'%20has%20been%20advocated%20by%20leaders%20of%20the%20ruling