20worker%2C%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20know%20that%20the%20police%20are%20just%20following%20orders.%20We%20want%20to%20question%20the%20higher%20ups.%20Do%20we%20have%20no%20rights%3F%E2%80%9D%20Rani%20(26)%20objected%20to%20this%2C%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20a%20problem%20with%20the%20police%20too%E2%80%A6%20they%20badly%20beat%20up%20a%20woman%20a%20few%20%3Cem%3Egalis%20%3C%2Fem%3Edown.%20Male%20policemen%20cannot%20hurt%20a%20woman%2C%20no%20matter%20what.%E2%80%9D%20The%20policy%20explicitly%20forbids%20violence%20against%20women%20and%20disabled%20people%20during%20the%20process%20of%20a%20demolition.%20It%20also%20mandates%20the%20DUSIB%20%E2%80%9Cshould%20ensure%20safe%20and%20affordable%20access%20to%20essential%20services%20%E2%80%93%20potable%20water%2C%20sanitation%20and%20health%E2%80%9D.%20Mohanty%20said%20that%20none%20of%20these%20services%20had%20been%20present%2C%20and%20temporary%20shelter%20and%20relief%20was%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20need%20of%20the%20hour%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08132018%2FSR7.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22904%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08132018%2FSR7.jpg%20904w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08132018%2FSR7-300x224.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688281%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22676%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPolice%20personnel%20supervising%20the%20demolition%20keep%20a%20strict%20check%20on%20people%20going%20into%20and%20leaving%20the%20basti.%20Photo%3A%20Sukanya%20Roy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08135018%2FSR8.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%22904%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08135018%2FSR8.jpg%20904w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F12%2F08135018%2FSR8-300x224.jpg%20300w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-688290%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22676%5C%22%3E%3Cp%20class%3D%5C%22wp-caption-text%5C%22%3EPiles%20of%20household%20items%20left%20out%20on%20the%20road%2C%20in%20the%20wake%20of%20the%20demolition.%20Photo%3A%20Sukanya%20Roy%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20minister%20of%20state%20for%20housing%20and%20urban%20affairs%2C%20Kaushal%20Kishore%2C%20refused%20to%20comment%20on%20the%20matter%20when%20called%20on%20the%20phone.%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Wire%3C%2Fem%3E%20also%20reached%20out%20to%20P.K.%20Jha%2C%20director%20of%20rehabilitation%20at%20DUSIB.%20He%20deemed%20rehabilitation%20to%20be%20solely%20the%20responsibility%20of%20the%20Delhi%20Development%20Authority%20(DDA).%20However%2C%20the%20DUSIB%20Act%20of%202010%20says%20otherwise.%20Sections%2010%20and%2012%20of%20the%20Act%20say%20that%20DUSIB%20has%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20power%20to%20prepare%20a%20scheme%20for%20the%20removal%20of%20any%20jhuggi%20jhopri%20basti%20and%20for%20resettlement%20of%20the%20residents%20thereof%E2%80%9D%2C%20adding%20that%20it%20may%20also%20%E2%80%9Cwork%20out%20schemes%20for%20collective%20community%20rehabilitation%2C%20relocation%20or%20in-situ%20upgradation%E2%80%A6%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20night%20fell%2C%20a%20street%20light%20at%20the%20entrance%20of%20Sunder%20Nagar%20was%20being%20repaired%20to%20serve%20as%20the%20sole%20source%20of%20light.%20Electricity%20had%20been%20cut%20off%20during%20the%20demolition%2C%20and%20will%20likely%20never%20be%20restored.%20Mona%20(20)%2C%20Falak%E2%80%99s%20sister%2C%20sat%20in%20their%20car