tps%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EOn%20September%2021%2C%20Lok%20Sabha%20MP%20Ramesh%20Bidhuri%20of%20the%20Bharatiya%20Janata%20Party%20(BJP)%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fnews%2Fnational%2Fopposition-demands-suspension-of-bjp-mp-bidhuri-over-communal-slurs%2Farticle67333929.ece%5C%22%3Ehurled%20communal%20slurs%20and%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E%C2%A0at%20Bahujan%20Samaj%20Party%20(BSP)%20member%20Danish%20Ali%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBidhuri%E2%80%99s%20remarks%20were%20expunged%20from%20the%20records%2C%20but%20despite%20Opposition%20pressing%20for%20his%20suspension%2C%20only%20a%20%E2%80%98warning%E2%80%99%20by%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20Speaker%20was%20given.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Fsuspended-lok-sabha-mp-count-nearly-doubles-during-nda-terms-data%2Farticle67388672.ece%5C%22%3EAs%20per%20data%20collated%20by%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20official%20statistics%20show%20that%20%E2%80%9Cmembers%20from%20non-BJP%20parties%20have%20been%20suspended%20for%20less%20severe%20offences%20in%20the%20recent%20past.%E2%80%9D%20While%20referring%20to%20the%20Mahabharata%2C%20Congress%20member%20Adhir%20Ranjan%20Chowdhury%20had%20said%20that%20the%20%E2%80%9Cking%E2%80%9D%20should%20not%20be%20blind%20to%20what%20is%20happening%20against%20women%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhether%20in%20Hastinapur%20or%20Manipur.%E2%80%9D%20He%20was%20suspended%20on%20August%2010%20for%20%E2%80%9Cgross%2C%20deliberate%20and%20repeated%20misconduct.%E2%80%9D%20The%20Privileges%20Committee%20revoked%20his%20suspension%20on%20August%2030.%20Earlier%2C%20on%20July%2024%2C%20Rajya%20Sabha%20chairman%20Jagdeep%20Dhankhar%20suspended%20Aam%20Aadmi%20Party%20(AAP)%20member%20Sanjay%20Singh%20for%20the%20remainder%20of%20the%20monsoon%20session%20after%20Singh%20rushed%20to%20the%20well%20of%20the%20House%20and%20pointed%20at%20the%20chair%20amid%20sloganeering%20by%20Opposition%20MPs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20session-wise%20suspension%20of%20members%20in%20each%20term%20of%20the%20last%20four%20Lok%20Sabhas%20(UPA-I%2C%20from%202004%20to%202009%3B%20UPA-II%2C%20from%202009%20to%202014%3B%20NDA-I%2C%20from%202014%20to%202019%3B%20and%20NDA-II%2C%20from%202019%20to%20present)%2C%20reveal%20that%20there%20have%20been%20144%20suspensions%20in%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%20in%20the%20past%20four%20terms.%20The%20first%2010-year%20period%20saw%2050%20suspensions%2C%20while%20the%20remaining%2094%20suspensions%20(65%25)%20took%20place%20during%20the%20NDA%E2%80%99s%20terms.%20No%20BJP%20members%20have%20been%20suspended%20during%20the%20NDA%E2%80%99s%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20a%20rising%20trend%20of%20MPs%20suspended%20in%20bulk%2C%20notes%20%3Cem%3EThe%20Hindu%3C%2Fem%3E.%20The%2016th%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%20elected%20in%202014%2C%20saw%20the%20highest%20number%20of%20suspensions%20(81)%20with%2049%20members%20being%20suspended%20in%20the%2016th%20session.%20The%20majority%20of%20suspended%20members%20belonged%20to%20the%20Congress%2C%20the%20All%20India%20Anna%20Dravida%20Munnetra%20Kazhagam%20(AIADMK)%20and%20the%20TDP%20(Telugu%20Desam%20Party).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ESeparation%20of%20powers%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20essence%20of%20a%20functional%20liberal%20democracy%20is%20the%20separation%20of%20powers%20between%20its%20pillars.%20Most%20important%20is%20the%20relationship%20between%20the%20legislature%20and%20the%20executive%2C%20as%20the%20executive%20is%20accountable%20to%20the%20legislature.%20Data%2C%20analysis%20and%20comments%20have%20found%20the%20record%20in%20the%20past%20ten%20years%20being%20a%20poor%20one.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20was%20brought%20to%20a%20focus%20in%20September%202020%2C%20when%20three%20controversial%20farm%20bills%20were%20passed%20without%20any%20division%20in%20the%20House%2C%20during%20a%20din%2C%20without%20the%20House%20being%20in%20order%2C%20no%20pre-legislative%20discussion%20or%20debate.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGlobal%20indices%20note%20inability%20to%20hold%20executive%20to%20account%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFunctioning%20of%20Parliament%20has%20drawn%20the%20attention%20of%20those%20studying%20Indian%20democracy%20and%20global%20indices%20which%20now%20count%20India%20as%20an%20%E2%80%9Celectoral%20autocracy%E2%80%9D%20(V-Dem).%20India%20has%20also%20been%20called%20out%20by%20IDEA%20International%20(which%20said%20civil%20liberties%20are%20now%20as%20they%20were%20in%201975)%2CFreedom%20House%20(which%20called%20India%20%E2%80%9Cpartly%20free%E2%80%9D)%20and%20The%20Economist%20index%20(in%20which%20India%20saw%20a%20sharp%20slump).%20The%202023%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Frights%2Findia-autocratiser-v-dem-report-2023%5C%22%3EV-Dem%20report%20refers%20to%20India%3C%2Fa%3E%20as%20%E2%80%9Cone%20of%20the%20worst%20autocratisers%20in%20the%20last%2010%20years%E2%80%9D%20in%20a%20blurb%20on%20page%2010%20and%20places%20India%20in%20the%20bottom%2040-50%25%20on%20its%20Liberal%20Democracy%20Index%20at%20rank%2097.%20India%20also%20ranks%20108%20on%20the%20Electoral%20Democracy%20Index%20and%20123%20on%20the%20Egalitarian%20Component%20Index.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20inability%20of%20Parliament%20to%20hold%20the%20executive%20(BJP-led%20Union%20government)%20to%20account%20is%20an%20important%20reason%20for%20the%20slide.%20IDEA%20International%20recorded%20last%20year%20that%20the%20effectiveness%20of%20parliament%20fell%2C%20and%20%E2%80%9Cby%209.6%25%E2%80%9D.%20IDEA%20International%20has%20been%20evaluating%20democracies%20since%201975%20and%20has%20a%20Global%20State%20of%20Democracy%20Index%20(or%20the%20GSoD)%20it%20releases%20which%20measures%20aspects%20of%20a%20democracy%2C%20vital%20to%20its%20health%20and%20survival.%20It%20records%20that%20India%20has%20%E2%80%9Csuffered%20decreases%20in%20all%20of%20the%20sub-attributes%E2%80%9D%20of%20the%20metric%20of%20checks%20on%20government%2C%20namely%20Effective%20Parliament%2C%20Judicial%20Independence%20and%20Media%20Integrity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOf%20the%20five%20indices%20used%20by%20V-Dem%20to%20capture%20democratic%20values%2C%20the%20deliberative%20democracy%20index%2C%20which%20measures%20whether%20political%20decisions%20are%20made%20through%20public%20reasoning%20or%20emotional%20appeals%20and%20coercion%2C%20has%20recorded%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thehindu.com%2Fdata%2Fdata-indias-democratic-values-have-eroded-significantly-v%25C2%25ADdem%2Farticle66644673.ece%5C%22%3Ea%20sharp%20slump%20since%202014.%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%E2%80%98%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fdeliverypdf.ssrn.com%2Fdelivery.php%3FID%3D393024093024068085064005002091095065035087048051093061101007104064106069068002005009007006111015121111108088016112088006002025117014070089021002086101006075111067096089054047120103083001115090020127094024102091078126080106112031089014011127028001096024%26EXT%3Dpdf%26INDEX%3DTRUE%5C%22%3EKilling%20a%20Constitution%20with%20a%20Thousand%20Cuts%E2%80%99%2C%20analysis%20by%20Professor%20Tarunabh%20Khaitan%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20then%20at%20the%20faculty%20of%20law%2C%20Oxford%20University%20found%20erosion%20of%20the%20power%20of%20the%20Opposition%20and%20their%20inability%20to%20function%20as%20they%20should%20be%20able%20to%20do%20in%20parliament%20since%202014.%20This%20was%20detrimental%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20democracy%2C%20he%20concluded.%20%E2%80%9CNot%20only%20did%20the%20BJP%20government%20seek%20to%20undermine%20electoral%20accountability%20to%20the%20citizens%2C%20it%20also%20systematically%20assaulted%20institutions%20that%20seek%20horizontal%20accountability%20from%20the%20political%20executive.%20These%20political%20institutions%20provided%20a%20voice%20to%20the%20Opposition%2C%20and%20therefore%20invited%20frequent%20%E2%80%9Dconstitutional%20hardball%E2%80%9D%20tactics%20from%20the%20government.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E2023%3A%20Disqualifications%20of%20MPs%20%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELakshadweep%20MP%20P.P.%20Mohammed%20Faisal%20of%20the%20Nationalist%20Congress%20Party%20and%20Waynad%20MP%20Rahul%20Gandhi%20of%20the%20Congress%20party%20were%20disqualified%20in%202023%2C%20but%20returned%20soon%20after%20convictions%20announced%20by%20the%20courts%20in%20their%20cases%20were%20overturned.%20A%20special%20MP%2FMLA%20court%20sentenced%20Ram%20Shankar%20Katheria%2C%20BJP%20MP%20from%20Etawah%2C%20for%20two%20years%20in%20an%20assault%20and%20rioting%20case%20this%20year%2C%20but%20he%20was%20not%20disqualified%20as%20he%20managed%20to%20obtain%20a%20stay.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702031420000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F30123153%2Fimage3-1.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdata-rewind-a-shadow-on-parliaments-ability-to-function-independently-of-the-executive%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Data%20on%20suspension%20of%20MPs%2C%20other%20analysis%20and%20accounts%20reveal%20that%20parliament%20functioning%20independently%20of%20the%20ruling%20party%20is%20an%20important%20component%20of%20a%20healthy%20democracy.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fgovernment%2Fdata-rewind-a-shadow-on-parliaments-ability-to-function-independently-of-the-executive%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Assam%20Citizenship%20Case%3A%20SC%20Tells%20Union%20Govt%20to%20Give%20Details%20on%20Undocumented%20Immigrants%20in%20Northeast%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20The%20Supreme%20Court%20has%20directed%20the%20Union%20government%20to%20furnish%20data%20on%20the%20inflow%20of%20immigrants%2C%20illegally%2C%20to%20the%20northeastern%20states%20after%20March%2024%2C%201971%2C%20and%20inform%20it%20about%20the%20steps%20taken%20at%20an%20administrative%20level%20to%20deal%20with%20the%20issue%2C%20particularly%20in%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20directives%20have%20come%20during%20the%20hearing%20of%20a%20bunch%20of%20petitions%20opposed%20to%2C%20and%20in%20support%20of%2C%20Section%206A%20inserted%20into%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%201955%20with%20the%20approval%20of%20Parliament%20for%20the%20state%20of%20Assam.%20Section%206A%20of%20the%20Act%20was%20accepted%20by%20Parliament%20in%20tandem%20with%20the%20memorandum%20of%20agreement%2C%20popularly%20known%20as%20the%20Assam%20Accord%2C%20signed%20in%201985%20between%20the%20leaders%20of%20the%20anti-foreigner%20agitation%20in%20the%20state%20and%20the%20Union%20and%20state%20governments%20to%20address%20the%20issue%20of%20immigrants%20entering%20the%20state%20without%20documents.%20The%20section%20allows%20foreign%20migrants%20to%20become%20Indian%20citizens%20if%20they%20had%20entered%20Assam%20till%20January%201%2C%201966%2C%20adding%20the%20provision%20that%20those%20who%20had%20entered%20after%20that%20date%20till%20March%2024%2C%201971%2C%20should%20also%20be%20considered%20for%20citizenship%20provided%20they%20are%20registered%20and%20their%20voting%20rights%20deferred%20for%20two%20consecutive%20terms.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhile%20several%20petitions%20are%20in%20support%20of%20the%20section%20approved%20by%20Parliament%2C%20some%20others%20are%20opposed%20to%20it%20on%20the%20ground%20that%20there%20should%20be%20a%20common%20citizenship%20rule%20for%20the%20entire%20country%2C%20and%20allowing%20such%20immigrants%20to%20become%20citizens%20and%20voters%20in%20Assam%20would%20change%20the%20state%E2%80%99s%20demography%20and%20thereby%20affect%20the%20local%20community%E2%80%99s%20culture%2C%20language%20and%20political%20rights.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20day%20one%20of%20the%20hearing%20on%20December%205%2C%20the%20five-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20led%20by%20Chief%20Justice%20D.Y.%20Chandrachud%20had%20orally%20observed%20that%20the%20special%20section%20was%20enacted%20by%20Parliament%20for%20Assam%20considering%20humanitarian%20aspects%20due%20to%20the%20Liberation%20War%20of%20Bangladesh%20with%20which%20the%20north-eastern%20state%20shares%20a%20long%20border.%20The%20chief%20justice%20said%20it%20had%20to%20be%20seen%20in%20the%20light%20of%20the%20vital%20role%20that%20India%20played%20in%20the%20liberation%20of%20Bangladesh.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20CJI%20had%20stated%20that%20India%E2%80%99s%20role%20in%20that%20liberation%20movement%20seems%20to%20have%20led%20Parliament%20proceed%20on%20the%20basis%20that%20the%20immigration%20that%20took%20place%20due%20to%20it%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20purely%20be%20regarded%20as%20illegal%20but%20humanitarian.%20The%20constitutional%20bench%20also%20includes%20Justices%20Surya%20Kant%2C%20M.M.%20Sundresh%2C%20J.B.%20Pardiwala%20and%20Manoj%20Misra.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20then%20asked%20Solicitor%20General%20of%20India%20Tushar%20Mehta%20to%20provide%20details%20on%20how%20many%20people%20had%20benefitted%20from%20the%20section%20since%20its%20enactment%2C%20also%20noting%20that%20it%20has%20nothing%20in%20front%20of%20it%20to%20deduce%20that%20the%20cultural%20rights%20of%20the%20people%20were%20affected%20by%20such%20immigration.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20bench%20had%20orally%20remarked%20that%20the%20government%20of%20the%20day%20must%20be%20given%20some%20leeway%20to%20make%20compromises%20for%20the%20nation%E2%80%99s%20wellbeing%20and%20that%20can%E2%80%99t%20be%20judged%20on%20the%20basis%20of%20hindsight%20wisdom.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20December%202014%2C%20a%20three-judge%20bench%20of%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20framed%2013%20questions%20encompassing%20various%20issues%20around%20the%20constitutionality%20of%20Section%206A%2C%20including%20whether%20the%20cultural%20and%20political%20rights%20of%20the%20Assamese%20people%20were%20diluted%20by%20the%20provision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202015%2C%20the%20bench%20referred%20the%20case%20to%20a%20five-judge%20constitutional%20bench%20which%20has%20resumed%20the%20hearing%20early%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20hearing%20of%20the%20case%20comes%20at%20a%20time%20when%20the%20country%20is%20close%20to%20the%202024%20parliamentary%20elections%20when%20Narendra%20Modi%20would%20be%20seeking%20a%20third%20term.%20In%20the%20run-up%20to%20the%202014%20and%202019%20polls%2C%20the%20alleged%20threat%20of%20%E2%80%98illegal%20immigrants%E2%80%99%20(read%20Muslims%20from%20Bangladesh)%20on%20Assam%20and%20Bengal%20and%20the%20need%20for%20a%20provision%20in%20the%20Act%20to%20protect%20and%20grant%20citizenship%20to%20three%20groups%20of%20people%20including%20Hindus%20from%20Bangladesh%20in%20Assam%20and%20elsewhere%20were%20used%20as%20political%20tools%20by%20the%20ruling%20party%20during%20its%20campaigning.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20two%20of%20Modi%E2%80%99s%20ministers%20have%20reiterated%20that%20rules%20to%20implement%20the%20Citizenship%20Amendment%20Act%20(CAA)%20would%20be%20readied%20soon.%20This%20special%20provision%20is%20likely%20to%20come%20to%20the%20aid%20of%20a%20large%20swathe%20of%20voters%20across%20Bengal%20and%20Assam.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1702030523000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F31224356%2FSupreme-Court-II-png.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fassam-citizenship-case-sc-tells-union-govt-to-give-details-on-undocumented-immigrants-in-northeast%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20apex%20court%E2%80%99s%20directives%20have%20come%20during%20the%20hearing%20of%20a%20bunch%20of%20petitions%20opposed%20to%2C%20and%20in%20support%20of%2C%20Section%206A%20inserted%20into%20the%20Citizenship%20Act%201955%20with%