ntrols%3D1%26amp%3Bcolor%3Dred%26amp%3Bcc_lang_pref%3D%26amp%3Brel%3D0%26amp%3Bautohide%3D2%26amp%3Btheme%3Ddark%26amp%3B%5C%22%20data-origwidth%3D%5C%22480%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22270%5C%22%3E%3Cimg%20data-spai-excluded%3D%5C%22true%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ytimg.com%2Fvi%2FZWZo7LZA-KE%2Fmaxresdefault.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22YouTube%20player%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fdiv%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20standout%20feature%20of%20the%20song%20is%20the%20hook%20(chorus)%2C%20which%20Moko%20describes%20as%20%E2%80%9Ca%20lullaby%20that%20was%20sung%20to%20us%20as%20children%20by%20our%20grandparents.%E2%80%9D%20Sung%20in%20Tenyidie%2C%20an%20indigenous%20language%20spoken%20by%20the%20Chakhesang%20Naga%20tribe%2C%20it%20brings%20a%20certain%20serenity%20amidst%20the%20chaos.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThere%20are%20two%20verses%20in%20the%20song%2C%20which%20are%20very%20chaotic%20%E2%80%94%20talking%20about%20the%20war%20and%20what%20our%20people%20went%20through.%20So%20I%20wanted%20the%20chorus%20to%20be%20very%20soothing%20and%20calm.%20When%20the%20chorus%20comes%20in%20after%20the%20first%20verse%2C%20it%E2%80%99s%20like%20putting%20the%20baby%20to%20sleep.%20You%20feel%20that%20calmness.%20And%20then%20the%20second%20verse%20comes%20in%20which%20talks%20about%20the%20war%20against%20the%20Japanese%2C%20which%20again%20is%20very%20violent%20and%20chaotic.%20This%20is%20once%20again%20followed%20by%20the%20chorus%20and%20the%20calmness%2C%E2%80%9D%20explains%20Moko.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CInitially%2C%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20know%20what%20to%20say%20in%20the%20chorus.%20It%20so%20happened%20that%20I%20was%20watching%20a%20short%20documentary%20about%20Naga%20folk%20music%20when%20I%20heard%20that%20lullaby.%20This%20was%20perfect%20for%20my%20song.%20After%20this%2C%20I%20got%20in%20touch%20with%20my%20friend%20Nourhe%20Zatsu%20who%20sang%20the%20chorus%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CLike%20Moko%E2%80%99s%20gr